curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " You should use  **kwargs  for that. \n\n  def test_func(arg1, *args, **kwargs):\n    optional_arg = kwargs.get(&#39optional_arg&#39)\n    ...\n  \n\n The only limitation is that the keyworded argument (optional_arg) must always be after keywordless arguments \n\n  &gt;&gt;&gt; test_func(\"foo\", optional_arg=\"bar\", arg1, arg2, ...)\n  File \"&lt;stdin&gt;\", line 1\nSyntaxError: non-keyword arg after keyword arg\n&gt;&gt;&gt; test_func(\"foo\", arg1, arg2, ..., optional_arg=\"bar\")\n...\n&gt;&gt;&gt; test_func(\"foo\", arg1, arg2, ...)\n...\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "07/17/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/17/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "07/17/2012", "id": "125", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to define method with optional argument and argument unpacking?", "parent_id": "11518149", "comment_count": 0, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "42127", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "math", "owner_user_id": "42127"},{"body": " This the  MSDN tutorial  contains all the JSON related operation.  \n\n Good Luck \n\n Chamath Jeevan \n", "last_activity_date": "05/15/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "05/15/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "126", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "C# JSON deserializing to Custom Class", "parent_id": "16558640", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "chamathjeevan", "owner_user_id": "442070"},{"body": "  public class AlternatingRowsConverter : IValueConverter\n\\{\nprivate bool _alternate;\n\npublic object Convert(object value, Type targetType, object parameter,\n           System.Globalization.CultureInfo culture)\n\\{\n  _alternate = !_alternate;\n  return _alternate\n        ? new SolidColorBrush(Color.FromArgb(255, 255, 0, 0))\n        : new SolidColorBrush(Color.FromArgb(255, 0, 0, 255));\n\\}\n\npublic object ConvertBack(object value, Type targetType, object parameter,\n             System.Globalization.CultureInfo culture) \n\\{ throw new NotImplementedException(); \\}\n \\}\n\\}\n  \n\n Then, listbox template: \n\n    &lt;ListBox ItemsSource=\"\\{Binding\\}\"\n       x:Name=\"Mylistbox\"\n       SelectionChanged=\"Mylistbox_SelectionChanged\"&gt;\n    &lt;ListBox.ItemTemplate&gt;\n      &lt;DataTemplate&gt;\n        &lt;StackPanel&gt;\n          &lt;Grid Background=\"\\{Binding Converter=\\{StaticResource alternateConvertor\\}\\}\"&gt;\n            &lt;TextBlock Grid.Column=\"0\"\n                  Text=\"\\{Binding Name, Mode=TwoWay\\}\"\n                  VerticalAlignment=\"Center\"\n                  HorizontalAlignment=\"Left\" /&gt;\n          &lt;/Grid&gt;\n        &lt;/StackPanel&gt;\n      &lt;/DataTemplate&gt;\n    &lt;/ListBox.ItemTemplate&gt;\n  &lt;/ListBox&gt;\n  \n\n and finally define the convertor object in the resource dictionary \n\n     &lt;phone:PhoneApplicationPage.Resources&gt;\n    &lt;WindowsPhoneApplication5:AlternatingRowsConverter x:Key=\"alternateConvertor\" /&gt;\n   &lt;/phone:PhoneApplicationPage.Resources&gt;\n  \n\n  More info here  \n", "last_activity_date": "07/18/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/18/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "127", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to apply alternative rows backgrounds in listbox items in windows phone 7?", "parent_id": "11534749", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Abhay Kumar", "owner_user_id": "646844"},{"body": " I guess there are some uses for a simple echo, but in any kind of a realistic interaction its going to be pretty hard to isolate just the piece you are trying to test. \n\n A more general approach would be to use a local proxy server, stands as the man in the middle\nbetween you and all remote sites, and can log urls, responses, content and so on.  \n\n If youre developing the server side as well as the client, you definitely ought to run a\nlocal mirror of the server site. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/10/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/10/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "128", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Is there a web service that spits out the entire request that was sent?", "parent_id": "11909148", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "ddyer", "owner_user_id": "172821"},{"body": " You could try using  document.stylesheets  to add css dynamically to your stylesheets. \n\n  styleSheet = document.styleSheets[0];\nstyleSheet.addRule(selector, style);\n  \n\n You could also use inline styles (id recommend this approach). \n\n You can change the width of an element using JavaScript like this. \n\n  elem.style.width = \"100px\";\n  \n\n And using jQuery \n\n  $(\"#selector\").css(\"width\", \"100px\");\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "07/18/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/18/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "129", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How can I create alike css classes", "parent_id": "11536537", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Sam", "owner_user_id": "1065786"},{"body": " PVS Studio will highlight if a structure can be reduced in size by reordering members.\n http://www.viva64.com/en/pvs-studio/ \nNot free but has free trial \n\n Its an addon for Visual Studio \n", "last_activity_date": "07/18/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/18/2012", "votes_count": 8, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "130", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Code analysis tool for optimal member layout", "parent_id": "11542152", "comment_count": 1, "score": 8, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Richard", "owner_user_id": "19897"},{"body": " The only way I can think of accomplishing this is to calculate the width and height every time the user enters text into the Text widget and then set the size of the widget to that. But the limitation here is that only mono-spaced fonts will work correctly, but here it is anyway: \n\n  import Tkinter\n\nclass TkExample(Tkinter.Frame):\n   def __init__(self, parent):\n      Tkinter.Frame.__init__(self, parent)\n      self.init_ui()\n\n   def init_ui(self):\n      self.pack()\n      text_box = Tkinter.Text(self)\n      text_box.pack()\n      text_box.bind(\"&lt;Key&gt;\", self.update_size)\n\n   def update_size(self, event):\n      widget_width = 0\n      widget_height = float(event.widget.index(Tkinter.END))\n      for line in event.widget.get(\"1.0\", Tkinter.END).split(\"E&#39\\\\&#39n\"):\n         if len(line) &gt; widget_width:\n            widget_width = len(line)+1\n      event.widget.config(width=widget_width, height=widget_height)\n\nif __name__ == &#39__main__&#39:\n    root = Tkinter.Tk()\n    TkExample(root)\n    root.mainloop()\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "07/18/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/18/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "131", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Tkinter Resize text to contents", "parent_id": "11544187", "comment_count": 2, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "sc0tt", "owner_user_id": "220330"},{"body": " The returned block can be false if an exception is thrown while it&#39s instantiated. In your code, this may certainly come from this part :  Mage::helper(&#39forms&#39) . \nIn the config.xml file of your module, have you defined the helpers like this ? : \n\n  &lt;global&gt;\n    &lt;helpers&gt;\n        &lt;forms&gt;&lt;class&gt;Coupsmart_Coupon_Helper&lt;/class&gt;&lt;/forms&gt;\n    &lt;/helpers&gt;\n&lt;/global&gt;\n  \n\n Else, replace  forms  by the other code you used in the calls to  Mage::helper(&#39forms&#39)  (from what it seems, this should probably  rather looks like this :  Mage::helper(&#39coupsmart_coupon&#39) ) \n", "last_activity_date": "07/18/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/18/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "132", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "What causes a block to be false after instantiating (and not an object) in Magento?", "parent_id": "11544835", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "blmage", "owner_user_id": "1288415"}]'
