curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Try removing the following from the config: \n\n \n      location / &123;\n        root   html;\n        index  index.html index.htm;\n    &125;\n  \n \n", "last_activity_date": "07/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/30/2012", "votes_count": 6, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "166", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Nginx Passenger Not Visible Application Issue", "parent_id": "11723010", "comment_count": 1, "score": 5, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Brandon Jernigan", "owner_user_id": "1559132"},{"body": "  WITH Table (Name, LoginTime, Row) AS\n(\n    SELECT \n       Name,\n       LoginTime,\n       ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY Name ORDER BY LoginTime)\n    FROM SomeTable\n)\nSELECT \n   Name,\n   LoginTime\nFROM Table\nWHERE \n   Row &lt;= 3\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "07/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/30/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "167", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "SQL: select three rows for each distinct value", "parent_id": "11727648", "comment_count": 5, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Aushin", "owner_user_id": "1430983"},{"body": " I added this link beside the out-of-stock associated product: \n\n  http://localhost/mysite/index.php/productalert/add/stock/product_id/[associated_product_id]/uenc/[any_key]/\n  \n\n For e.g. \n\n  http://localhost/mysite/index.php/productalert/add/stock/product_id/17/uenc/MTM0MzcyMDk0Mw==/\n  \n\n It does my job.  \n\n Only thing is, after successfully adding the alert record, it redirects to home page, instead of same page as in normal case.  \n\n This is due to [any_key], if we could somehow encrypt current page url [the any_key] just like magento does, we can have it redirect to same page also, after successful saving of alert record.\nAny ideas? \n\n Thanks \n\n Ok I got it finally! \n\n The uenc key [any_key] is actually base64 encoding of current url. \n\n So with the help of  https://github.com/carlo/jquery-base64 , I did: \n\n  var encodedUrl = $.base64.encode(window.location);\n\nvar redirectTo = http://localhost/mysite/index.php/productalert/add/stock/product_id/[associated_product_id]/uenc/ + encodedUrl + /;\n  \n\n Hope this helps! \n", "last_activity_date": "07/31/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/31/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "07/31/2012", "id": "168", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "magento show &quot;Sign up to get notified when this product is back in stock&quot; link for simple-associated products", "parent_id": "11648920", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "212692", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Prashant", "owner_user_id": "212692"},{"body": " How fast is your disk subsystem? \n\n If you can read 40 MB per second, reading 1500 MB should take about 40 seconds. If you want to go faster than this, you need a faster disk subsystem. If you are reading from a local drive and its taking minutes, you have a tuning problem and there is not much you can doing Java to fix this because it is not the problem. \n\n You can use a memory mapped file instead, but this will only speed up the access if you dont need all the data. If you need it all, you are limited by the speed of your hardware. \n", "last_activity_date": "07/31/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "07/31/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "169", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Java - Read File in Byte Array", "parent_id": "11745535", "comment_count": 5, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Peter Lawrey", "owner_user_id": "57695"},{"body": " Postgres probably evaluates the subselect only once because technically theres no reason to evaluate it for every row.\nYou could force it by referencing a column from the drivers table into the subselect, like this: \n\n  SELECT\n    drivers.driver_id AS drivers_driver_id,\n    (\n        SELECT\n            drivers_names.name_en\n        FROM\n            drivers_names\n        ORDER BY random()+drivers.driver_id LIMIT 1\n    ) AS driver_name\nFROM\n    drivers\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/01/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/01/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "170", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Postgresql: Random value for a column selected frm second table", "parent_id": "11753873", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Daniel V\u00e9rit\u00e9", "owner_user_id": "238814"},{"body": " This is not possible, unless the other apps in question are providing some method for you to get this data. And AFAIK, no app provides such a feature. \n\n On a rooted device you could perhaps monitor incoming network data and see which app its going to and estimate the progress, but I doubt this could be turned into a proper app. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/13/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/13/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "171", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Calculate Percentage Downloaded and Time Remaining for in OTHER application", "parent_id": "11927853", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Raghav Sood", "owner_user_id": "1069068"},{"body": " What you can do is to actually emulate every scope (think method) on a sheet of paper, where you write down all the variables.  \n\n If you call a method you take a new piece of paper and put it on the stack of existing paper. If you return from a method you throw the top most piece a way. If you have classes you would need a separate sheet for those. \n\n That is what you could do. But no real programmer does that.  \n\n What you do instead is: \n\n \n  understand the basic structure from looking at the code. Things like: It will call \"witch\" a couple of time before it will print \"ghost\".  \n  for understanding the details you guide and double check your thoughts with logging/system out statements and / or the debugger and actually executing the code.  \n \n\n So is the exercise useless? Dont think so. While you dont do it on its own it is part of thinking about code and you do that all the time one way or the other. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/05/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/05/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "172", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "What sort of diagramming method could I use to keep everything organized while tracing through this program?", "parent_id": "11814096", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jens Schauder", "owner_user_id": "66686"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " To remove all whitespace between images like you want,  float  wont work. You could create three  column   &lt;div&gt;  tags and place your images within those columns. For instance, if you want three columns: \n\n HTML: \n\n  &lt;div class=\"imgCol\"&gt;\n    &lt;!-- every third image --&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=\"imgCol\"&gt;\n    &lt;!-- every third image --&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=\"imgCol\"&gt;\n    &lt;!-- every third image --&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n  \n\n Then, add  float: left;  to the CSS for your column class (in this case  .imgCol ) and ensure the widths and margins are such that the columns appear side by side and no float drop occurs. \n\n Heres a demo:   http://jsfiddle.net/yLRWK/   \n\n For your particular situation, you could implement this as follows. I dont code in ASP.net, so there is some pseudocode thrown in \n\n  &lt;div class=\"Forum\"&gt;\n    &lt;p&gt;The Forum&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;div class=\"imgCol\"&gt;\n        /* create counter = 0 */\n        @foreach (var item in Model) &123;                           \n            /* if counter % 3 == 0, then write img tag */     \n            &lt;img src=\"@item.Blog.Image.img_path\" alt=\"Not Found\" /&gt;\n            /* counter++ */\n        &125;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div class=\"imgCol\"&gt;\n        /* create counter = 0 */\n        @foreach (var item in Model) &123;                           \n            /* if counter % 3 == 1, then write img tag */     \n            &lt;img src=\"@item.Blog.Image.img_path\" alt=\"Not Found\" /&gt;\n            /* counter++ */\n        &125;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div class=\"imgCol\"&gt;\n        /* create counter = 0 */\n        @foreach (var item in Model) &123;                           \n            /* if counter % 3 == 2, then write img tag */     \n            &lt;img src=\"@item.Blog.Image.img_path\" alt=\"Not Found\" /&gt;\n            /* counter++ */\n        &125;\n    &lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n  \n\n There may be a better solution that does not require looping through the images three times, but that is best left to someone that better knows ASP.net \n", "last_activity_date": "08/06/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/06/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "173", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Line up nested div tags", "parent_id": "11830676", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "jackwanders", "owner_user_id": "293403"},{"body": "  Contains()  is not among  Stringbuilders methods . That said, you have a couple options... \n\n 1.: Test your values on the way in and maintain a boolean flag for your  append  &lt;br&gt;  tags  state. \n\n 2.: Perform  ToString()  and call  Contains()  from the result: \n\n  if strMsg.ToString().Contains(\"&lt;table&gt;\") then ...\n  \n\n 3.: Implement  IndexOf()  and/or  Contains()  yourself: \n\n  Module StringBuilderExtensions\n\n    &lt;Extension()&gt;\n    Public Function IndexOf(ByVal sb As StringBuilder, ByVal value As String) As Integer\n\n        For i As Integer = 0 To sb.Length - value.Length - 1\n\n            For y As Integer = 0 To value.Length - 1\n\n                If value(y) &lt;&gt; sb(i + y) Then\n\n                    Exit For\n\n                ElseIf y = value.Length - 1 Then\n\n                    Return i\n\n                End If\n\n            Next\n\n        Next\n\n        Return -1\n\n    End Function\n\n    &lt;Extension()&gt;\n    Public Function Contains(ByVal sb As StringBuilder, ByVal value As String) As Boolean\n\n        Return sb.IndexOf(value) &gt; -1\n\n    End Function\n\nEnd Module\n  \n\n  Disclaimer : This hasnt been tested for performance... and Michael Harens comment was directed at the  ToString()  option. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/07/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/06/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "08/07/2012", "id": "174", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "VB stringbuilder Contains", "parent_id": "11832176", "comment_count": 2, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "621962", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "canon", "owner_user_id": "621962"},{"body": " I dont think you should reinvent the wheel and write your side scheduler. You need to add the HazardRecognizer in your backend. This way LLVMs scheduler will know about possible hazards and will try to avoid them. PPC backend is probably the best example of such scheduling. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/07/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/07/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "175", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "llvm scheduling to prevent data hazards", "parent_id": "11841253", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Anton Korobeynikov", "owner_user_id": "164925"},{"body": " Use  #inject  \n\n  hashes = [&123;\"testPARAM1\"=&gt;\"testVAL1\"&125;, &123;\"testPARAM2\"=&gt;\"testVAL2\"&125;]\nmerged = hashes.inject(&123;&125;) &123; |aggregate, hash| aggregate.merge hash &125;\nmerged # =&gt; &123;\"testPARAM1\"=&gt;\"testVAL1\", \"testPARAM2\"=&gt;\"testVAL2\"&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/08/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/08/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "176", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Rails mapping array of hashes onto single hash", "parent_id": "11856407", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Joshua Cheek", "owner_user_id": "184212"},{"body": " If it is useful to have state in your conversion, use a class. Preferably, a functor so you can pass an instance around as a callable entity. If there is no state, then use a function. \n\n As an aside, your signature and return type should probably look like this: \n\n  int ConvertStrToInt(const std::string&amp; str);\n  \n\n  Edit  concerning this particular example, the C++ standard library provides this functionality already, so you dont need to re-implement it. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/08/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/08/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "08/08/2012", "id": "177", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Using a function or class in c++ for a simple task?", "parent_id": "11860173", "comment_count": 2, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "661519", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "juanchopanza", "owner_user_id": "661519"},{"body": " Assuming that  data  contains your data, this could do the job: \n\n  with open(\"data\") as f:\n        lines=[line.strip().split() for line in f]\ncombinations=&123;&125;\nfor combination in lines[1:]:\n        key=\", \".join([lines[0][i]\n                for i in xrange(len(combination))\n                if combination[i] != 0])\n        combinations[key]=combinations.setdefault(key, 0)+1\nfor key, value in combinations.iteritems():\n        print value, E&#39\\\\&#39t, key\n  \n\n or, using the collections module: \n\n  import collections\n\nwith open(\"data\") as f:\n        lines=[line.strip().split() for line in f]\n\ncombinations=collections.Counter(\n        \", \".join(lines[0][i]\n                for i in xrange(len(combination))\n                        if combination[i] != 0)\n                for combination in lines[1:])\n\nfor key, value in combinations.iteritems():\n        print value, E&#39\\\\&#39t, key\n  \n\n  EDIT:  Another version saving resources using a generator expression \n\n  import collections\n\nwith open(\"data\") as f:\n        lines=(line.strip().split() for line in f)\n        header=next(lines)\n        combinations=collections.Counter(\n                \", \".join(header[i]\n                        for i in xrange(len(combination))\n                                if combination[i] != 0)\n                        for combination in lines)\n        for key, value in combinations.iteritems():\n                print value, E&#39\\\\&#39t, key\n  \n\n Im sure this could be improved. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/09/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/08/2012", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "08/09/2012", "id": "178", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Computing the combinations for presence or absence of a factor in a table", "parent_id": "11863759", "comment_count": 4, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "589206", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "hochl", "owner_user_id": "589206"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " VS has never been good with remote ASP debugging. Maybe this will help fellow developers still debugging classic ASP. Ive been using a tool for classic asp debugging called team remote asp debugger for over 8 years now, very highly recommended, I think its the only classic asp debugger out there that actually allows remote asp debugging without attaching to process. I think the link is still the same  http://www.remotedebugger.com \n Hope this helps.\n Cheers,\n Angelo \n", "last_activity_date": "08/08/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/08/2012", "votes_count": 6, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "179", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Debugging Classic ASP in Visual Studio 2010", "parent_id": "3453762", "comment_count": 1, "score": 6, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Angelo Di Varro", "owner_user_id": "1586186"},{"body": " You simply cant run App Store-applications on the Simulator. \nThe iOS Simulator is intended for developers: you can only run apps of which you have the source on the simulator. The App Store binary is compiled for ARM while the simulator expects an Intel-build. The only way to get it run is compiling it for Intel which is impossible without the source code. \n", "last_activity_date": "11/23/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "11/23/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "180", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Unable to run an ipad application", "parent_id": "13535283", "comment_count": 3, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "s1m0n", "owner_user_id": "1336645"},{"body": " The code you posted has some significant security issues: \n\n \n A user can simply disable Javascript to prevent being redirected. \n A user can simply add  ?register.php  to the URL to avoid triggering the redirect code. \n \n\n Instead, use a server-side session variable check. If a logged in flag is not set within the session, then you redirect to the login page. \n\n This has 2 massive advantages:  \n\n \n the logged in state is kept somewhere where the user cant do anything to manipulate it, EXCEPT by logging in \n If a malicious user just trashes the session cookie, theyll just get a new blank session and be considered \"not logged in\", and just get redirected again anyways. \n \n", "last_activity_date": "08/12/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/12/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "08/12/2012", "id": "181", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Requiring login to access my Wordpress site", "parent_id": "11918896", "comment_count": 5, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "212218", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Marc B", "owner_user_id": "118068"},{"body": " DDE has long since been deprecated. \n\n On Google you will find many questions about DDE not working on Windows 7. \nSuggested solutions have included: \n\n \n Disabling UAC. \n  Registering DDE messages in the message filter of the receiving program \n\n  ChangeWindowMessageFilter(WM_DDE_FIRST, MSGFLT_ADD);\n...\nChangeWindowMessageFilter(WM_DDE_LAST, MSGFLT_ADD);\n   \n Elevating the sending programs permissions. \n \n\n See if any of that works for you. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/12/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/12/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "182", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "dde excel 2010 links don&#39;t all work", "parent_id": "11864305", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "GSerg", "owner_user_id": "11683"},{"body": " Two errors: \n\n See the missing name in the HTML for the textarea. Corrected code: \n\n  &lt;textarea name=\"message\" class=\"message\"&gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;\n  \n\n For the code you dont end your assignment to $email_body with a semicolon but appended to it by a dot. Just a bit of luck that you didnt end up with a parse error. Corrected code: \n\n  $email_body = \"You have received a new message from the user $name.E&#39\\\\&#39n\".\n\"Here is the message:E&#39\\\\&#39n $message\";\n\n$to = \"info@sodium3.com\";\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/12/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/12/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "183", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "very simple php issue I need assistance with", "parent_id": "11925217", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Clarence", "owner_user_id": "1099675"},{"body": " You could add this code to the Created() event for the entity: \n\n  partial void Readings_Created()\n&123;\n    ReadingDate = (from o in this.DataWorkspace.Data.Readings\n                  where MeterID == this.MeterID\n                  orderby o.ReadingDate descending\n                  select o).Take(1).Execute().Max(o =&gt; o.ReadingDate).AddDays(1);\n&125;\n  \n\n I tested a similar set of code and it calculated the correct date for the new row.  I did not test if this could would work if there are no entries for the MeterID. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/13/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/13/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "184", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Auto-Increment Date on new row in Lightswitch", "parent_id": "11937712", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Registered User", "owner_user_id": "38332"},{"body": " I think you are overthinking this problem. You should be able to just do this: \n\n  NSURL *thumbnailURL = [NSURL URLWithString:[[thumbnails objectAtIndex:indexPath.row] URLString]]];\n\n[cell.imageView setImageWithURL:thumbnailURL\n               placeholderImage:[UIImage imageNamed:@\"placeholder\"]];\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/13/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/13/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "185", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Integrating SDWebImage With YouTube Api", "parent_id": "11942799", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "jonkroll", "owner_user_id": "663476"},{"body": " Im afraid Androids Virtual Machine memory used for each application is quite limited: 16MB in most cases and 24MB for some other. I also came across that limitation. First you should check that your application has no memory leaks. If thats not enough then you may need to consider forcing calls to the garbage collector:  http://docs.xamarin.com/android/advanced_topics/garbage_collection . You should also bear in mind that calling GC will make your application slower. \n\n If anyone has a better option Id be very happy to know about it! \n", "last_activity_date": "08/14/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/14/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_