curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Since regex solution has been given by Sean, \n\n Here is my previous project regex I used, \n\n  $regex= \"/^[.a-z0-9_E&#39\\\\&#39-]+[@][a-z0-9_E&#39\\\\&#39-]+([.][a-z0-9_E&#39\\\\&#39-]+)+[a-z]&123;1,4&125;$/i\";\n  \n\n This is another alternative for PHP mailing, you will need to download phpmailer plugin in order for this mailing to work. \n\n  &lt;?php\n// mail config start \n\n$emailAddress = youremailhere;\n$replyAdress =yourreceipientemailhere;\n$replyName = yourreceipientname;\n$msgSubject= yoursubjecthere;\n\n\n// mail config end \n\n// Include the class,\nrequire \"phpmailer/class.phpmailer.php\";\n\n//Type your message here:\n$msg = blablayourmessagehere;\n\n//The mailing process begins!!\n$mail = new PHPMailer();\n$mail-&gt;IsMail();\n\n$mail-&gt;AddReplyTo($replyAdress, $replyName);\n$mail-&gt;AddAddress($emailAddress);\n$mail-&gt;SetFrom($replyAdress, $replyName);\n$mail-&gt;Subject = \"New: \".$replyName.\" have sent a \".$msgSubject.\" message\";\n\n$mail-&gt;MsgHTML($msg);\n\n$mail-&gt;Send();\n\n?&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/29/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/29/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "08/29/2012", "id": "214", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "PHP contact form not validating or sending", "parent_id": "12169912", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1631889", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Furry", "owner_user_id": "1631889"},{"body": "   &lt;Window.Resources&gt;\n    &lt;ph:PhotoList x:Key=\"MyPhotos\"  Path=\"D:E&#39\\\\&#39Visual Studio ProjectsE&#39\\\\&#39WPF APPLICATIONSE&#39\\\\&#39ImageViewerE&#39\\\\&#39ImageViewerE&#39\\\\&#39Images\"&gt;      \n    &lt;/ph:PhotoList&gt;    \n &lt;/Window.Resources&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "09/10/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/10/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "215", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Setting ListBox ItemsSource to an object from StaticResource as shown in MSDN", "parent_id": "12356561", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Slugart", "owner_user_id": "142182"},{"body": " I found the answer mostly with help from a co-worker and also some with various stack overflow posts. I was concerned with not only seeing the answer but what exactly was going on with the commands. \n\n Below sets the DateTime variable to the local date and time in yyyymmdd_hhmmss This code is correctly used being placed in your script. \n\n  for /f \"skip=1\" %%c in (wmic os get LocalDateTime) do set DateTime=%%c\nset DateTime=%DateTime:~0,8%_%DateTime:~8,6%\n  \n\n \n\n Explanation:\nIf you run the below command in cmd \n\n  wmic os get LocalDateTime\n  \n\n you get the output of (different numbers depending on the date/time you do this): \n\n  LocalDateTime\n20120829151726.702000-300\n  \n\n Now we need to format this. For this purpose I only care for the date and time. The second line has the date and time in the format yyyymmddhhmmss with some extra gobbly goop. We obviously dont want the first line and we dont want the .702000-300. \n\n To remove this we need to format. By using  \"skip=1\" ,you are skipping the first line. The :~#,# helps you to choose which characters to use (Dont actually use the # character, Im only using that as a placeholder so you know a number goes there). The first # is your starting value and the second # is the number of characters after the starting value. We want to use the first 8 characters for the date (yyymmdd) and therefore we have the starting value as 0 (the first #) and the second # as 8.  \n\n I then add the underscore and the information needed for the 6 characters for the time (hhmmss). \n\n Within your script you can now have the code to call the DateTime variable. \n\n  echo Hello!&gt;&gt;BestFileEver_%DateTime%.txt\n  \n\n Now the text file with the word hello in it will have the file name below:     \n\n  BestFileEver_20120829_153326.txt\n  \n\n Now obviously the numbers will be different depending on the time you did this. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/29/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/29/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "216", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "how do I make the txt output from a .cmd file contain the current date and time in the filename?", "parent_id": "12148137", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Patrick", "owner_user_id": "413267"},{"body": " I think that is the your image url problem. I have used another image, check this fiddle\n http://jsfiddle.net/J9bjm/514/  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/30/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "217", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Show some text on content div(image)", "parent_id": "12181150", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Sowmya", "owner_user_id": "1033200"},{"body": " \n   from comment by Arjuna Del Toso: \n  \n   You can use a column in the WHERE clause only if its marked as \"indexable\" \n \n\n Not, that is not totally correct. \n\n You need  at least one  indexable column in your where clause \u2013 once you have that, you can use other, non-indexed columns as well to further restrict the result. \n\n \n\n Since the user\u2019s current profile picture is always the  album cover photo  of their  Profile Pictures  album, we can use that to get the  object_id  of the profile picture of our friends, and than use that to select the info we want from the  photo  table: \n\n  SELECT owner, src_small, created FROM photo WHERE object_id IN (\n  SELECT cover_object_id FROM album WHERE owner IN (\n    SELECT uid1 FROM friend WHERE uid2 = me()\n  ) AND name = Profile Pictures\n)\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "08/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/30/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "218", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "get profile picture creation date from user table in fql", "parent_id": "12192247", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "CBroe", "owner_user_id": "1427878"},{"body": "  $protocol = current(explode(/,$_SERVER[SERVER_PROTOCOL]));\n  \n\n If you really just want to know if it HTTPS is enabled or not, you can just use  $_SERVER[HTTPS] . \n", "last_activity_date": "08/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/30/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "219", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to get the protocol in php?", "parent_id": "12202894", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "kba", "owner_user_id": "453331"},{"body": " You will need to set  AutoPostback  to true. \nBut you can use an update panel to do a partial PostBack and not refresh the complete page. \n\n  See here   \n\n Use it like this: \n\n  &lt;asp:UpdatePanel ID=\"UpdatePanel1\" runat=\"server\" UpdateMode=\"Always\" ChildrenAsTriggers=\"true\" &gt;      \n  &lt;ContentTemplate&gt;\n    &lt;asp:DropDownList ID=\"DropDownList1\" runat=\"server\" AutoPostBack=\"True\"  onselectedindexchanged=\"DropDownList1_SelectedIndexChanged\"&gt;\n      &lt;asp:ListItem&gt;item 1&lt;/asp:ListItem&gt;\n      &lt;asp:ListItem&gt;item 2&lt;/asp:ListItem&gt;\n    &lt;/asp:DropDownList&gt;\n  &lt;/ContentTemplate&gt;\n&lt;/asp:UpdatePanel&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "09/01/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/01/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "220", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to Save Data without Page Reloading on Dropdown SelectedIndexChanged Event", "parent_id": "12228505", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "nunespascal", "owner_user_id": "88896"},{"body": " Do this: \n\n  1. Go to target seetings of your project.\n\n2. Now go to Build settings. In Search bar type \" Other Linker Flags \". As shown below in image will appear on screen.\n  \n\n   \n\n Now add -all_load to both Debug and Release. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/03/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/03/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "221", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Admob Integration", "parent_id": "12241680", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Prince", "owner_user_id": "1106035"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Yes, under comments there is a like entry. Check out \n http://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/api/Comment/  \n", "last_activity_date": "10/02/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "10/02/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "222", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Tracking Facebook Post Like", "parent_id": "12683436", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "AronVietti", "owner_user_id": "1588643"},{"body": " Well, since my comment  is  the actual answer to your question, Ill just post it here:  the  WHITESPACE_ONLY  compilation might well be the least invasive of all  compilation modes  but as the docs clearly state: \n\n \n   The WHITESPACE_ONLY compilation level removes comments from your code and also removes line breaks, unnecessary spaces, and other whitespace. The output JavaScript is functionally identical to the source JavaScript. \n \n\n From  the docs, on compilation modes . As you can read on this page, the  WHITESPACE_ONLY  compilation returns the most human-readable code of all modes. All other modes execute the  WHITESPACE_ONLY  compilation, and do other stuff in addition to that. To answer your question: No, there is no way to tell the compiler to leave excessive white-space unchanged for some code, and go crazy on other parts of your code. The only thing you  can  do is write a script, that extracts the object literals you want preserved and save them to a separate file. After compiling the original, you can replace the in-lined versions of those object literals with their \"white-space-heavy\" counterparts.  \n\n But since youre so keen on keeping your code readable, Id strongly suggest either  not  minifying anything, or use the  pretty-print  button in your console, twined with the other neat features the console provides you with to inspect objects.  An even better approach would be: to write your code, and test it extensively and only minify/compile  for production  (IE: when youre done with the coding/debugging). After all, thats how these tools were meant to be used. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/03/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/03/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "223", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "google closure compiler, PRETTY_PRINT and object literal", "parent_id": "12246417", "comment_count": 4, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Elias Van Ootegem", "owner_user_id": "1230836"},{"body": " I just had the same error message while trying to build wireshark on OSX Lion. It looks like GNU gettext provides libintl. In my case, I had installed gettext via homebrew, but the symlinks were not in place, so running: \n\n  brew link gettext\n  \n\n fixed the problem for me. \n\n If you dont have  gettext  installed, you may want to install it, either using  homebrew  or otherwise. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/03/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/03/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "224", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "ld: library not found for -lintl on mac os x lion", "parent_id": "11151197", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "m01", "owner_user_id": "1298153"},{"body": " See:  http://jsfiddle.net/M8y5J/  \n\n \n fix syntax errors \n load when  document is ready  (note multiple ways of doing this) \n  use  on()  to attach event handler  \n \n\n JavaScript \n\n  $(function()&123;\n    $(\"#target\").on(\"keypress\", function(e)&123;   \n        if ( e.which === 13 ) &123;\n            alert(\"Enter has been clicked.\");\n        &125;\n    &125;);\n&125;);\n  \n\n Full HTML \n\n  &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n    &lt;head&gt;\n        &lt;title&gt;Demo&lt;/title&gt;\n        &lt;script type=text/javascript src=http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.8.0.js&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n        &lt;script type=\"text/javascript\"&gt;\n            $(function () &123;\n                $(\"#target\").on(\"keypress\", function (e) &123;\n                    if (e.which === 13) &123;\n                        alert(\"Enter has been clicked.\");\n                    &125;\n                &125;);\n            &125;);\n        &lt;/script&gt;\n    &lt;/head&gt;\n    &lt;body&gt;\n        &lt;input type=\"text\" id=\"target\" /&gt;\n    &lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "09/03/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/03/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "09/03/2012", "id": "225", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Give a message when clicking Enter", "parent_id": "12253319", "comment_count": 12, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "453277", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Tim Medora", "owner_user_id": "453277"},{"body": " Is it possible that you specified a node.js buildpack upon creating your app? \n\n  https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/buildpacks  \n\n Since you have a proper Gemfile, it should be detected by the ruby buildpack first. Additionally, since you dont have a package.json file, Node.js should not be detected. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/06/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/06/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "226", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Heroku detects my sinatra app as a node.js application and fails", "parent_id": "12288714", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ylan S", "owner_user_id": "965723"},{"body": " This is because you have for loop Syntax \n\n  int tail;\n  \n\n for( tail = 0 ; tail &lt; len; tail++ ) \n&123; \n        str[tail] = 0;                                                                                 &125; \n\n The first parameter is the initializer so if you have initialized the variable then you have keep empty the initializer space and put the semicolon instead. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/06/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/06/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "227", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Why is there a semi-colon right after this for loop?", "parent_id": "12293988", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "ovais", "owner_user_id": "1507187"},{"body": " I would imagine you could just assign the value in the code behind. \n\n e.g.; \n\n  ASPxPopupControl_Surveill.ContentUrl = \"~/PopUp/Surveillance.aspx?SoinId=\" + Request[\"SoinId\"].ToString();\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "09/24/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/24/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "228", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "how can i pass the querystring into aspx", "parent_id": "12566652", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Tim B James", "owner_user_id": "177988"},{"body": "  If you want to sell features of the app you will have to use IAP (read the iOS guidelines).  If you are going to sell real products or services which are independent to your app (like web services) you arent not allowed to use IAP and you must use something like WePay.  \n\n If you want to sell real products or web services setup a web based shop which uses WePay (with the PHP SDK) and let the app just interact with your web shop.  \n\n Another approach would be implementing it directly inside the app. I would strongly advise against implementing the payment process directly inside the app. This would be stupidly easy to hack since your customers can change the binary of your app. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/06/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/06/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "09/06/2012", "id": "229", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "WePay payment gateway integration in IOS", "parent_id": "12303252", "comment_count": 3, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1037200", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "miho", "owner_user_id": "1037200"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " If you really need a  Label , you can use the code below. Otherwise I would suggest a   StyledText   (as mentioned in the comments): \n\n  public static void main(String[] args) &123;\n    final Display display = new Display();\n    final Shell shell = new Shell(display);\n    shell.setLayout(new FillLayout());\n\n    Label label = new Label(shell, SWT.NONE);\n    label.setText(\"Blue and not blue\");\n\n    Color blue = display.getSystemColor(SWT.COLOR_BLUE);\n\n    final TextLayout layout = new TextLayout(display);\n    layout.setText(\"Blue and not blue\");\n    final TextStyle style = new TextStyle(display.getSystemFont(), blue, null);\n\n    label.addListener(SWT.Paint, new Listener() &123;\n        @Override\n        public void handleEvent(Event event) &123;\n            layout.setStyle(style, 0, 3);\n            layout.draw(event.gc, event.x, event.y);\n        &125;\n    &125;);\n\n    shell.pack();\n    shell.open();\n    while (!shell.isDisposed()) &123;\n        if (!display.readAndDispatch()) &123;\n            display.sleep();\n        &125;\n    &125;\n    display.dispose();\n\n&125;\n  \n\n With  StyledText  it would look something like this: \n\n  public static void main(String[] args) &123;\n    final Display display = new Display();\n    final Shell shell = new Shell(display);\n    shell.setLayout(new FillLayout());\n\n    StyledText text = new StyledText(shell, SWT.NONE);\n    text.setEditable(false);\n    text.setEnabled(false);\n    text.setText(\"Blue and not blue\");\n\n    Color blue = display.getSystemColor(SWT.COLOR_BLUE);\n\n    StyleRange range = new StyleRange(0, 4, blue, null);\n\n    text.setStyleRange(range);\n\n    shell.pack();\n    shell.open();\n    while (!shell.isDisposed()) &123;\n        if (!display.readAndDispatch()) &123;\n            display.sleep();\n        &125;\n    &125;\n    display.dispose();\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "09/08/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/08/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "09/08/2012", "id": "230", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Changing color of certain words in a SWT Label?", "parent_id": "12331271", "comment_count": 7, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "1449199", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Baz", "owner_user_id": "1449199"},{"body": " Is this over a serial line? May be a mismatched baudrate, parity, data/stop bit or flow control handshake problem. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/09/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/09/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "231", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "What kind of encoding is this (not base64)?", "parent_id": "12336363", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Charlie", "owner_user_id": "1657618"},{"body": " There is nothing built in to CSS to cover both of these:  http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-selectors/#combinators .  Anything that LESS may provide would be a js extension. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/10/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/10/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "232", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "CSS nth-child conditioning using LESS?", "parent_id": "12354322", "comment_count": 1, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Matt Whipple", "owner_user_id": "1655332"},{"body": "    pass.push(document.getElementById(\"passcode\").value,[We can chat here.]);\n\n