is: &123;0&125;\", httpRes.StatusDescription);\n        // Releases the resources of the response.\n        httpRes.Close();\n    &125;\n&125;\ncatch (WebException ex) &123;\n    Console.WriteLine(\"Error returned: &123;0&125;\",ex.Response);\n    // can throw again here.\n    throw;\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "11/28/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "11/28/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "11/28/2012", "id": "340", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How do I determine if internet file exists on server?", "parent_id": "13595888", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "494340", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Gerard Sexton", "owner_user_id": "494340"},{"body": " This is because Windows API  MoveFile  and related functions can also be used to move directories, but  CopyFile  and related functions cannot be used with directories. \n\n More fundamentally, this is because moving a file or directory is just renaming it; it doesnt actually require physically moving the files (or files) data on the disk.  When you rename a directory, the files that it contains automatically pick up the new path \"by reference\", as it were.  Its not necessary to operate on each files entry. \n", "last_activity_date": "11/29/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "11/29/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "341", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Why .net does not have method to copy an entire directory", "parent_id": "13619145", "comment_count": 0, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "phoog", "owner_user_id": "385844"},{"body": " The other side doesnt have the ignore file in