b Fanger", "owner_user_id": "19165"},{"body": " I suggest you use sanitize the strings for SQL injections using  mysql_real_escape_string() . Validate using if else statements. Fore example \n\n  if ($_POST[name]...) \n&123;\n    echo \"fill in those fields!\";\n&125;\nelse\n&123;\n    do stuff...\n&125;\n  \n\n By the way you should be using a PDO prepared statement and not echoing HTML with PHP.  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/28/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/28/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "378", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "validating data in PHP", "parent_id": "11483989", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "James A. Anderson", "owner_user_id": "1431587"},{"body": " According to the C++ standard long needs to be at least as large as an int. This means that long can also be the same size as an int, which then implies that the min and max for a long and int of the same type (signed or unsigned) can be equal. \n\n More info (not just about long and int, but other types as well) here:  http://stackoverflow.com/a/271132/13760  \n\n Here is some more interesting reading:  Is `long` guaranteed to be at least 32 bits?  \n\n As far as question 2 is concerned, you need to check your project settings and see if youre building a Win32 or x64 executable. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/16/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/16/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "12/16/2012", "id": "379", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "c++ maximum of number types", "parent_id": "13905717", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "13760", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Carl", "owner_user_id": "13760"},{"body": " I had the same issue on my android version 4.0.3.\nChanging the min sdk version to 7 did the trick. \n\n  &lt;uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion=\"7\" /&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/17/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/17/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "12/17/2012", "id": "380", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "&quot;Sending Email in Android using JavaMail API without using the default/built-in app&quot; only works on emulator?", "parent_id": "12916867", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "322283", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "sara", "owner_user_id": "1821233"},{"body": " The line \n\n  Employer(last_name, first_name, address, phone, email)\n  \n\n creates an  Employer  object that is immediately garbage-collected as the execution of  __init__()  ends. It does not affect the  Intern  object in any way. What you mean is probably something like \n\n  Employer.__init__(self, last_name, first_name, address, phone, email)\n  \n\n or maybe \n\n  super(Intern, self).__init__(last_name, first_name, address, phone, email)\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/17/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/17/2012", "votes_count": 7, "last_edit_date": "12/17/2012", "id": "381", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Something wrong with Python class Inheritance", "parent_id": "13919022", "comment_count": 6, "score": 6, "last_editor_user_id": "1258041", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Lev Levitsky", "owner_user_id": "1258041"},{"body": " I got it: \n\n Your query is very confusing since it does not include the MONTH column: \n\n If you would have done that, you would have realized your query is not ordered by MONTH and so, the MONTH 12 is returned as the 3rd row of your query. \n\n ;) \n\n  select SUM(totalsellingprice) from dbo.tblServiceOrders\ngroup by datepart(MONTH,dbo.tblServiceOrders.datereceived)\norder by datepart(MONTH,dbo.tblServiceOrders.datereceived)\n  \n\n And please, dont refer to the row index to choose which month is related to which sum. And should be a good idea to also discriminate the year (if you need to). \n", "last_activity_date": "12/19/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/19/2012", "votes_count": 7, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "382", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "using datepart() with the group by command", "parent_id": "13957170", "comment_count": 5, "score": 6, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Francis P", "owner_user_id": "1286013"},{"body": " Pure DDD is about making implicit explicit, ie : not using List(), but rather ListTheCustomerThatHaveNotBeSeenForALongTime(). \n\n What is at stake here is a technical implementation. From What I know, domain driven design does not provide technical choices. \n\n Generic repository fits well. Your use of this generic repository might not fit the spirit of ddd though. It depends on your domain. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/26/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/26/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "383", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Generic Vs Individual Repository for Aggregate Root", "parent_id": "14032834", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Arthis", "owner_user_id": "259240"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " You can use CipherOutputStream and CipherInputStream to encrypt or decrypt Input/A  \n\n  CipherInputStream  is composed of an InputStream and a Cipher so that read() methods return data that are read in from the underlying InputStream but have been additionally processed by the Cipher. The Cipher must be fully initialized before being used by a CipherInputStream. \n\n For example, if the Cipher is initialized for decryption, the CipherInputStream will attempt to read in data and decrypt them, before returning the decrypted data. \n\n This class adheres strictly to the semantics, especially the failure semantics, of its ancestor classes java.io.FilterInputStream and java.io.InputStream. This class has exactly those methods specified in its ancestor classes, and overrides them all. Moreover, this class catches all exceptions that are not thrown by its ancestor classes. In particular, the skip method skips, and the available method counts only data that have been processed by the encapsulated Cipher. \n\n It is crucial for a programmer using this class not to use methods that are not defined or overriden in this class (such as a new method or constructor that is later added to one of the super classes), because the design and implementation of those methods are unlikely to have considered security impact with regard to CipherInputStream. \n\n A  CipherOutputStream  is composed of an OutputStream and a Cipher so that write() methods first process the data before writing them out to the underlying OutputStream. The cipher must be fully initialized before being used by a CipherOutputStream. \n\n For example, if the cipher is initialized for encryption, the CipherOutputStream will attempt to encrypt data before writing out the encrypted data. \n\n This class adheres strictly to the semantics, especially the failure semantics, of its ancestor classes java.io.OutputStream and java.io.FilterOutputStream. This class has exactly those methods specified in its ancestor classes, and overrides them all. Moreover, this class catches all exceptions that are not thrown by its ancestor classes. \n\n It is crucial for a programmer using this class not to use methods that are not defined or overriden in this class (such as a new method or constructor that is later added to one of the super classes), because the design and implementation of those methods are unlikely to have considered security impact with regard to CipherOutputStream. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/19/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/19/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "384", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "En/Decrypting an In/Output stream in Java?", "parent_id": "13960927", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Abhishekkumar", "owner_user_id": "1569443"},{"body": " Are you running into this problem when building on TFS?  \n\n If so, I experienced the same problem today: \n\n  Could not find the Conceptual Schema node to embed as a resource for input file ...\nCould not find the Storage Schema node to embed as a resource for input file ...\nCould not find the Mapping node to embed as a resource for input file ...\n  \n\n Our  resident build expert  informed me the TFS build server did not have .NET 4.5 loaded. \n\n To resolve the problem, I set the project properties to .NET 4.0 instead of .NET 4.5, regenerated my EDMX file/service, and successfully built/checked-in. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/19/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/19/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "385", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Could not find the Conceptual Schema node to embed as a resource for input file", "parent_id": "13422851", "comment_count": 1, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Mike", "owner_user_id": "1375478"},{"body": " Multiple inheritance is not possible in PHP like in many  OOP  supported languages  \n\n See similar topic  here . The topic is in  AS3  but gives you answer. \n\n To answer particularly about solving using interfaces is answered in the same post  here  \n\n Hope this helps \n", "last_activity_date": "12/20/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/20/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "12/20/2012", "id": "386", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "PHP Multiple Inheritance with Interfaces", "parent_id": "13966054", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "572270", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Noob AS Three Developer", "owner_user_id": "310967"},{"body": " Logger will inherit all appenders from root. You need to specify level only: \n\n  &lt;root&gt;\n    &lt;level value=\"INFO\"/&gt;\n    &lt;appender-ref ref=\"RollingFileAppender\"/&gt;\n&lt;/root&gt;\n&lt;logger name=\"AutoTagCore.net.windward.autotag.utils\"&gt;\n    &lt;level value=\"DEBUG\"/&gt;\n&lt;/logger&gt;\n  \n\n  BTW  Verify appender settings - it could be restricted to INFO level: \n\n  &lt;threshold value=\"INFO\"/&gt;\n  \n\n And last possible issue - you can have different type namespace and logger name (maybe some typo). \n", "last_activity_date": "12/20/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/20/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "12/20/2012", "id": "387", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How do I configure log4net for a different level for some classes?", "parent_id": "13980615", "comment_count": 10, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "470005", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "lazyberezovsky", "owner_user_id": "470005"},{"body": " Functionally, the two ways of doing this are equivalent. The decorator syntax is just syntactic sugar. \n\n  @some_decorator\ndef some_func():\n    ...\n  \n\n ...is equivalent to... \n\n  def some_func():\n    ....\nsome_func = some_decorator(some_func)\n  \n\n The decorator syntax makes your code more cleaner (the non-decorator syntax means you have to type \"some_func\" three times!) and your intent more obvious, so Id say definitely use the decorator syntax. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/20/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/20/2012", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "388", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Should Python&#39;s property() be used as a decorator or saved to a variable?", "parent_id": "13982054", "comment_count": 2, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "tom", "owner_user_id": "665575"},{"body": " SFML 2.0 rectangle types were changed from (left, top, right, bottom) to (left, top, width, height). I make that mistake too all the time. \n\n To move the camera around all you need to do is to move the  sf::View . In your code that is as simple as calling  CameraPosition.setCenter(x, y); . \n", "last_activity_date": "12/21/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/21/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "12/21/2012", "id": "389", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "SFML 2.0 equivalent of SetFromRect()?", "parent_id": "13998320", "comment_count": 8, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1801919", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Andrei Tita", "owner_user_id": "1801919"},{"body": " Always check in FTP connection strings that you put a double slash after host name and before the path, e.g. ftp.mickeymouse//htdocs/filename. \n\n When I had onlty one slash maqrk I got a totally unhelpful error 550 message. \n\n Solved my problems, though it may not be relevant here. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/22/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/22/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "390", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "VB.NET FTP Error 550", "parent_id": "10813700", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Owler", "owner_user_id": "1923705"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " You  can  use globbing with  :edit  and other commands; however, there must be a  single, unique result  of the glob, because the  :edit  command only takes a single file. (How else should it display multiple matches in the single current window?) \n\n If you want to edit multiple files sequentially, you can use  :args  or  :argadd  instead. Note that the  :split  command does not take multiple files, neither (probably because of the risk that many matches will inadvertently cause an impractically large number of window splits), but you could write your own  :Split  command that provides this functionality. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/26/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/26/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "391", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Why vim disallows globbing with :e command?", "parent_id": "14034625", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ingo Karkat", "owner_user_id": "813602"},{"body": " Do you want to create a custom list like this image ? OR a web part ? \n\n If you like to create a list like this I am afraid its not possible \n\n but If you like to create a web part then you have to create Custom web part or Visual web part which will fetch data and display as per your requirement. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/26/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/26/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "392", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to configure multicolumn header in sharepoint list?", "parent_id": "14031524", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "SigarDave", "owner_user_id": "1249386"},{"body": " Its not entirely clear whats happening here. Youve provided plenty of information but not everything needed to give a definitive answer. Ill try to address your questions first: \n\n \n   Do I have to invalidate the timer when the application starts sleeping\n  (computer goes in standby),and create another one when it returns on? \n \n\n Have to? No. Should for cleanliness and certainty of the state? Yes, probably. You should probably specify exactly how you set up the timer since you can run into problems with it interacting with the run loop ... but I dont think this is your problem. \n\n \n   The label is updated in the main queue, so I still have to protect the\n  label access with a mutex? \n \n\n As long as you update the UI from the main thread/queue, you should be fine. This is a standard design approach with blocks. \n\n \n   Sometimes the panels are missing: at the start of the application I am\n  able to launch panels by clicking a menu item, but sometimes they are\n  not launching.I dont know how to reproduce this bug always, it just\n  happens randomly when the application is active for 2/3 hours usually,\n  I have to relaunch the application to go around this. \n \n\n If you dont know how to reproduce it, Im not sure we can help you beyond \"places to look.\" The first thought Ive got is that you may be recreating multiple copies of your primary controllers when the app becomes active (since you asked about this earlier, I assume youve tried doing something with it). Make sure the same controllers are being reused. \n\n Now on to the code. \n\n  NSOperationQueue* queue=[NSOperationQueue new];\n  \n\n The  queue  variable is local to the scope of the method. I see no retain/release, so I assume youre using ARC. In that case, youre not retaining the new queue youre creating and its life span is not guaranteed to survive as long as you need it to once the method completes and youve left its scope. You should make  queue  an instance variable so it sticks around. This way the queue can be reused every time the method is fired and itll stay around long enough for other queues/threads to use.  \n\n I think its likely  this  is your biggest culprit. Adjust it and update your question to reflect how it affects the condition of your app. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/22/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/22/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "393", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Status application: sometimes panels are missing, multithreading possible issue", "parent_id": "13992184", "comment_count": 8, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Joshua Nozzi", "owner_user_id": "201199"},{"body": " Im a new SO user, and therefore I cant comment on the question itself, but I think I can help.  Forgive me if I post an answer that is actually a comment, but I think thats my best option.  Ill edit this question to become an answer once things have been clarified. \n\n Your phrase, \"I imported a database to my wordpress dashboard\" doesnt exactly make sense.  Where was the data initially?  What sort of data was in it?  What tool are you using to do the import? \n", "last_activity_date": "12/27/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/27/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "394", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Failed to import \u201cContact form 1\u201d: Invalid post type wpcf7_contact_form Failed to import Media \u201cdb_site.sql_.txt\u201d", "parent_id": "12589905", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Noah Dyer", "owner_user_id": "1929225"},{"body": " You have a race condition problem.More info (I know it talks about visual basic, just skip these things) here . \nTo solve it you need a mutex, declare it as global variable:   \n\n  pthread_mutex_t mux;  \n  \n\n Initialize it:   \n\n  pthread_mutex_init(&amp;mux,NULL);\n  \n\n Then use it for reading the shared variable:   \n\n  void count()\n&123;\n    int i=0;\n    for(i=0; i&lt;NITERS; i++)\n    &123;\n        pthread_mutex_lock(&amp;mux);\n        cnt++;\n        pthread_mutex_unlock(&amp;mux);\n    &125;\n    pthread_exit(0);\n&125;\n  \n\n All this because there are two threads incrementing the same variable, they fetch the variables before incrementing it and they put it in a register.So they value that they are reading isnt unique: every thread has its own copy so each thread may ignore the change of the other, until they effectively write it to its address in the memory. \n NB  : If you want that the thread update the variable in an ordered way (i.e.: thread 1 counts to NITERS without being interrupted, when thread 2 starts counting), you have to lock the mutex before the for. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/22/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/22/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "395", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Thread can&#39;t count, giving wrong result", "parent_id": "14004993", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ramy Al Zuhouri", "owner_user_id": "570339"},{"body": " The Jar files in the projects lib folder should be matching the version of iReport\n I had the same problem and it has been solved by using correct jar files.\n you can take a look at the link below:\n http://sourceforge.net/projects/jasperreports/files/jasperreports/  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/24/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/24/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "396", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Exception in JasperPrint in JasperReport", "parent_id": "7776968", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "AhmadNasrElKaffas", "owner_user_id": "1926513"},{"body": " You should use something like: \n\n  public &lt;T&gt; T inject(Class&lt;T&gt; clazz);\n  \n\n When using  T  instead of  ?  you can return a object of type  T  \n\n By the way this is the same what  Injector  does: \n\n  public abstract T getInstance (Class&lt;T&gt; type)\n  \n\n  Note : In your code you try to implement an abstract method. You should remove the abstract keyword or you will get a syntax error. Abstract methods cannot contain an implementation (this is done in sub classes). \n", "last_activity_date": "12/24/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/24/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "12/24/2012", "id": "397", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to wrap Google Guice&#39;s Injector methods?", "parent_id": "14024183", "comment_count": 2, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "1115554", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "micha", "owner_user_id": "1115554"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " i once studied matlab at engineering school and i think you need to link the output of your sinusoid to a box called minmax \n\n  http://www.mathworks.com/help/simulink/slref/minmax.html  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/25/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/25/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "398", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to get max from Scope (Simulink)", "parent_id": "14031198", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "cristi _b", "owner_user_id": "879063"},{"body": " Put in in the model (School): \n\n  def reviews_average\n  reviews.average(:rating).round(1) unless reviews.blank?\nend\n  \n\n View:  \n\n  &lt;%= @school.reviews_average %&gt;\n  \n\n  Reason:  Do not put DB intensive procedures into the view because the rendering speed depends on it. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/25/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/25/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "399", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Where should I put this, in the model, a helper, or a controller?", "parent_id": "14031339", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Valery Kvon", "owner_user_id": "1222782"},{"body": " If you simply need to be able to export your workflow exactly \"as is\" as part of a solution then: \n\n Go to Customisations  >  Solutions >  [open your solution] >  Components >  Processes \n\n Next to the \"Add new\" button there is an \"Add Existing\" button which allows you to select components from the Default Solution. \n\n Note that this does not change the schema name of the workflow. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/25/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/25/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "400", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How can I move a workflow into a solution?", "parent_id": "14030675", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Greg Owens", "owner_user_id": "1045988"},{"body": " I set this up once and documented what I did here \n\n  http://blog.alvazan.com/165/how-to-set-up-the-cassandra-wordcount-example/  \n\n it could be out of date.  We will be doing another example with PlayOrm for cassandra eventually as well with its NoSql entities (uses nosql patterns instead of relational patterns though with some relational ones). \n\n Dean \n", "last_activity_date": "12/26/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/26/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "401", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Cassandra Hadoop Integration and Wordcount Example", "parent_id": "14045318", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Dean Hiller", "owner_user_id": "517781"},{"body": " I fired up a new project and installed the grid via the nuGet package and it looks to me is that you are causing a conflict with the default resource bundler that is setup with MVC4 projects by default now. You will either need to remove the following line from the Views/Shared/_Layout file: \n\n  @Scripts.Render(\"~/bundles/jquery\")\n  \n\n Which will remove the bundled scripts. \n\n Or add your jqGrid script references to the bundle config in the App_Start folder, and then remove the script tags from your view. \n\n  bundles.Add(new ScriptBundle(\"~/bundles/jquery\").Include(\n                            \"~/Scripts/jquery-&123;version&125;.js\",\n                            \"~/Scripts/i18n/grid.locale-en.js\",\n                            \"~/Scripts/jquery.jqGrid.min.js\"));\n\n&lt;!----Remove These From your view-------!&gt;\n&lt;script src=\"~/Scripts/jquery-1.7.2.min.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;script src=\"~/Scripts/i18n/grid.locale-en.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;script src=\"~/Scripts/jquery.jqGrid.min.js\"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/28/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/28/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "402", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Unable to get jquery.jqgrid 4.4.1 working in ASP.NET MVC", "parent_id": "14064492", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Chad Ferguson", "owner_user_id": "480659"},{"body": " make the ads background images and than use background cover \n\n  #divname&123;\nbackground: url(images/bg.jpg) no-repeat center center fixed; \n    -webkit-background-size: cover;\n    -moz-background-size: cover;\n    -o-background-size: cover;\n    background-size: cover;\n    min-height:0%;\n    max-height:100%;\n\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/29/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/29/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "403", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "solution for div causing x scrolling in browsers", "parent_id": "14083915", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ivo Jonkers", "owner_user_id": "1655941"},{"body": " Override the getView method. If you look at the source code of CursorAdapter ( link ), youll see a place where they check if the view is null. You just need to copy the whole method, and add an additional if check for  ts.getRunning() == id  \n\n Here is how it should now look like -  \n\n  public View getView(int position, View convertView, ViewGroup parent) &123;\n    if (!mDataValid) &123;\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\"this should only be called when the cursor is valid\");\n    &125;\n    if (!mCursor.moveToPosition(position)) &123;\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\"couldnt move cursor to position \" + position);\n    &125;\n    View v;\n    if (convertView == null || ts.getRunning() == id) &123;\n        v = newView(mContext, mCursor, parent);\n    &125; else &123;\n        v = convertView;\n    &125;\n    bindView(v, mContext, mCursor);\n    return v;\n&125;\n  \n\n Thankfully, it looks like all the fields used in that method are protected, so you should not run into any problems.  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/30/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "404", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Prevent re-use of some views in ListView (custom cursor-adapter)", "parent_id": "14091423", "comment_count": 2, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Abhinav", "owner_user_id": "526635"},{"body": "  getSharedPreferences()  requires a valid Context, so the earliest you can run this code is in  onCreate() : \n\n  // Create the SharedPreferences object\nSharedPreferences prefs;\n\n// Create the Preference Editor object\nSharedPreferences.Editor prefsEditor;\n\n@Override\nprotected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) &123;\n    ...\n    prefs = getSharedPreferences(\"settings\", MODE_PRIVATE);\n    prefsEditor = prefs.edit();\n  \n\n \n\n I may have answered a question like this before for you, so a good rule of thumb is: only try to set primitive variables outside of your methods. Variables like  int ,  long , or even  String  are safe. But be wary of any data type that starts with a capital letter, ( String  is the one exception). \n", "last_activity_date": "12/30/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/30/2012", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "405", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "SharedPreferences -- Where do the intial values come from with a new app?", "parent_id": "14095838", "comment_count": 2, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Sam", "owner_user_id": "1267661"},{"body": " I finally solved this using: \n\n  $ cd /usr/local/Cellar/imagemagick/6.8.0-10/lib\n$ ln -s libMagick++-Q16.7.dylib   libMagick++.dylib\n$ ln -s libMagickCore-Q16.7.dylib libMagickCore.dylib\n$ ln -s libMagickWand-Q16.7.dylib libMagickWand.dylib\n  \n\n The solution comes from  https://coderwall.com/p/wnomjg  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/31/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/31/2012", "votes_count": 10, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "406", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Issue with installing ImageMagick and rmagick on Mountain Lion", "parent_id": "11676844", "comment_count": 0, "score": 10, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "balexand", "owner_user_id": "239965"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " If youre going for rich functionality like selection, grouping, sorting, etc. then use the solution @Louis_PIG answered with. If you need very basic horizontal layout like that, then use  disply:-ms-flexbox  CSS display property. If you create a div and set that, then all of its children will be laid out horizontally. Then you have all kinds of control over the children and their size and position. You can set their relative widths, distribute them equally, stretch them, and more. See  this  for lots of info on flexboxes. \n\n Heres a sample flexbox... \n\n  &lt;!-- HTML snippet --&gt;    \n&lt;div class=\"flex\"&gt;\n    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n    &lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div\n\n/* CSS snippet */\n.flex &123;\n    display: -ms-flexbox;\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/02/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/02/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "407", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "One Row, Multiple Column WinJS Layout", "parent_id": "14113281", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jeremy Foster", "owner_user_id": "1499273"},{"body": " You need to check to see if the change is value adjusting. \n\n Link to the full tutorial:\n http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/slider.html  \n\n But heres the important bit: \n\n  public void stateChanged(ChangeEvent e) &123;\n    JSlider source = (JSlider)e.getSource();\n    if (!source.getValueIsAdjusting()) &123;\n        // Do what needs to occur here.\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n Basically when getValueIsAdjusting() returns false, the user has stopped moving the slider. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/02/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/02/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/02/2013", "id": "408", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Java ChangeListener firing multiple times", "parent_id": "14127354", "comment_count": 1, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "213901", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Erik Nedwidek", "owner_user_id": "63386"},{"body": " Youve added a navigation property to your model and so EF is trying to map that to your database. \"Code First\" means your code model defines your database schema. \n\n Try adding the  [NotMapped]  attribute to your helper properties to tell EF to ignore them. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/03/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "409", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Entity Framework 5 - Invalid column name - Reverse Engineer Code First", "parent_id": "14142186", "comment_count": 2, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Nicholas Butler", "owner_user_id": "115098"},{"body": " This is very subjective. Id write, if I were following E501 strictly:  \n\n  field = TreeForeignKey(self,\n                       null=True,\n                       blank=True,\n                       related_name=abcdefgh)\n  \n\n I usually consider 100 too long, not 80. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/03/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "410", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Line is too long. Django PEP8", "parent_id": "14143284", "comment_count": 2, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Pavel Anossov", "owner_user_id": "830012"},{"body": " You are using the same  name  attribute on every row in the form, so they are being overridden and its using the last one. \n\n What you could do is either wrap every row in its own form, or you could do something like this, and have only 1 submit button to execute the action on every row: \n\n  // remove hidden id element\n\n...\n\necho \"&lt;td&gt;&lt;select name=action[\" . $row[0] . \"]&gt;\"\n\n...\n// remove submit button in the loop, but add it after the while loop\n...\n\nif (isset($_POST[action]))\n&123;\n    foreach ($_POST[action] as $id =&gt; $action)\n    &123;\n        if ($action !== choose)\n        &123;\n            // do action on the id;\n            echo $id . \" -&gt; \" . $action . \"&lt;br&gt;\";\n        &125;\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/03/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/03/2013", "id": "411", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Delete wrong record from table", "parent_id": "14148782", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "1296660", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Supericy", "owner_user_id": "1296660"},{"body": " You can create a  Containter View Controlller  that presents your controllers as you want. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/04/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "412", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How can I go from one ViewController to enother", "parent_id": "14155143", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "graver", "owner_user_id": "1228534"},{"body": " Try this: \n\n  eval echo \"E&#39\\\\&#39\"$&123;line//E&#39\\\\&#39\"/E&#39\\\\&#39E&#39\\\\&#39E&#39\\\\&#39\"&125;E&#39\\\\&#39\"\"\n  \n\n That should prevent the shell from doing anything more than variable substitution. I dread to think how many junk files your XML files produced with all those random  &gt;  redirects! \n", "last_activity_date": "01/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/04/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/04/2013", "id": "413", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to substitute shell variables in complex text files", "parent_id": "14155596", "comment_count": 5, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1057909", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "ams", "owner_user_id": "1057909"},{"body": " If youre planning on using your own custom back button, and are willing to link the back action manually, (which Im guessing you are because you added a nav bar in IB, not from the nav controller) you can use a  UIToolBar  instead. \n\n Tool bars support multiple buttons, and allow you to more precisely arrange them using fixed and flexible space UIBarButtonItems. \n\n   \n\n To do this to a navigation bar added by your navigation controller, you have to add the buttons programmatically: \n\n  UIBarButtonItem *myItem1 = [[UIBarButtonItem alloc] initWithBarButtonSystemItem:UIBarButtonSystemItemAction target:self action:@selector(someMethod)];\nUIBarButtonItem *myItem2 = [[UIBarButtonItem alloc] initWithBarButtonSystemItem:UIBarButtonSystemItemAdd target:self action:@selector(someMethod)];\n\n[[self navigationItem] setLeftBarButtonItems:[NSArray arrayWithObjects:myItem1,myItem2, nil]];\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/04/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/04/2013", "id": "414", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "add bar button item next to back button on navigational bar", "parent_id": "14160570", "comment_count": 3, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "716216", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "0x7fffffff", "owner_user_id": "716216"},{"body": " You can use  regex  to extract the values, I am not sure if this is what you are looking for but try this: \n\n  import re\n\np2 = \"&lt;x=-0.5478253364562988, y=-0.5376561880111694, z=1.7154035568237305, w=1.0&gt;\"\np2 = re.findall(\"-?E&#39\\\\&#39d+.E&#39\\\\&#39d+\",p2)\np2_xy = p2[0],p2[1]\nprint (\"p2\",p2_xy)\n  \n\n Output: \n\n  (ps, (-0.5478253364562988, -0.5376561880111694))\n  \n\n Or if you want a more cleaner version: \n\n  import re\n\np2 = \"&lt;x=-0.5478253364562988, y=-0.5376561880111694, z=1.7154035568237305, w=1.0&gt;\"\np2 = re.findall(\"-?E&#39\\\\&#39d+.E&#39\\\\&#39d+\",p2)\nprint (\"p2\",p2[0],p2[1])\n  \n\n Output: \n\n  (p2, -0.5478253364562988, -0.5376561880111694)\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/04/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "415", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Converting Python (PyKinect) Skeleton data to Point(X,Y)", "parent_id": "14144644", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "enginefree", "owner_user_id": "1786283"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " since you already have the option of setting  setClickable()  at your disposal. \n\n i assume you are wondering about any best practice. \n\n just curious, will not making the button  disabled  be more  intuitive  to the user about the situation. \n", "last_activity_date": "08/24/2011", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "08/24/2011", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "416", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Android + setOnClickListener sets setClickable to true by default?", "parent_id": "7169433", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Samuel", "owner_user_id": "398715"},{"body": " The only problem is in the way you set up your properties.  By default, private fields arent serialized, and public properties will only deserialize if you have a setter defined.  The setter itself can be public or private.  If youre concerned about initializing your list, just do it in the constructor. \n\n Here is the most simple approach: \n\n  public class Campaign : Entity\n&123;\n    public Campaign()\n    &123;\n        TrackingEntries = new Collection&lt;TrackingEntry&gt;();\n    &125;\n\n    public string BrandId &123; get; set; &125;\n\n    public ICollection&lt;TrackingEntry&gt; TrackingEntries &123; get; private set; &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n The same would work for any collection type.  (array, list, enumerable, etc) \n\n An alternative approach would be through attributing.  But I think the first approach is better because it keeps your entities free of dependencies, and is easier to read. \n\n  public class Campaign : Entity\n&123;\n    [JsonProperty(\"TrackingEntries\")]\n    private ICollection&lt;TrackingEntry&gt; trackingEntries;\n\n    public string BrandId &123; get; set; &125;\n\n    [JsonIgnore]\n    public ICollection&lt;TrackingEntry&gt; TrackingEntries\n    &123;\n        get &123; return trackingEntries ?? (trackingEntries = new Collection&lt;TrackingEntry&gt;()); &125;\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/06/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/06/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "417", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "RavenDB query not rehydrating enumerable property", "parent_id": "14182893", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Matt Johnson", "owner_user_id": "634824"},{"body": " There isnt really a good way you can do that with just a Javascript button.  A better choice would be a little Visualforce page which allows the agent to enter the comment and sets the status and owner accordingly on save. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/07/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "418", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Javascript SFDC Custom Case Button- Want &quot;new comment&quot; window to render in parent window like Close Case (Salesforce custom button)", "parent_id": "13980277", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "amrcn_werewolf", "owner_user_id": "671910"},{"body": " Try to use  ColorFilter : \n\n  Imagebutton.setColorFilter(0x808fd2ea);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/07/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "419", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to highlight a Bitmap? Like Google Play", "parent_id": "14198337", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "vmironov", "owner_user_id": "1950649"},{"body": " The MP4 files need to be encoded in H.264. I just downloaded the vid1.mp4 file, and did a quick property inspector view in QuickTime, and the file is encoded in MPEG-4, which is not something that Flash, or HTML5 supports. If you do a re-encode to H.264, it will work. You can re-encode using this tool -  http://handbrake.fr/  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/07/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "420", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "jwplayer: video plays but there&#39;s no display?", "parent_id": "14200775", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ethan LongTail", "owner_user_id": "1645000"},{"body": " This  blog  from perforce suggests  p4 move -f  is the way to go. (Although you might have to revert the deletes)  p4 move manual . \n", "last_activity_date": "01/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/07/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "421", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "perforce shelve examples", "parent_id": "14198621", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Douglas Leeder", "owner_user_id": "3978"},{"body": " ArrayList is part of java collection frame work. Since ArrayLis is an index based data-structure searching or getting element from Array with index is pretty fast. Array provides O(1) performance for get(index) method but remove is costly in ArrayList as you need to rearrange all elements. \n\n For more help on Java collection framework read below book \n\n  Java Collection  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/10/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/10/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "422", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Indexed based datastructure", "parent_id": "11607288", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Rais Alam", "owner_user_id": "1471203"},{"body": " You can use  array sorting  to sort the array. In your case I would choose  sort()  \n\n Now to show the links with a preceding Letter I would use: \n\n  &lt;?php\n$records = [Aaaaa, Aaaa2, bbb, bbb2, Dddd];\n$lastChar = ;\nsort($records, SORT_STRING | SORT_FLAG_CASE); //the flags are needed. Without the `Ddd` will come before `bbb`.\n//Available from version 5.4. If you have an earlier version (4+) you can try natcasesort()\n\nforeach($records as $val) &123;\n  $char = $val[0]; //first char\n\n  if ($char !== $lastChar) &123;\n    if ($lastChar !== )\n      echo &lt;br&gt;;\n\n    echo strtoupper($char).&lt;br&gt;; //print A / B / C etc\n    $lastChar = $char;\n  &125;\n\n echo $val.&lt;br&gt;;\n&125;\n?&gt;\n  \n\n This will output something like \n\n  A\nAaaa2\nAaaaa\n\nB\nbbb\nbbb2\n\nD\nDddd\n  \n\n Notice that the C is missing, because there are no words starting with C. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/08/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/08/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/08/2013", "id": "423", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Group array results in Alphabetic order PHP", "parent_id": "14210480", "comment_count": 3, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "434949", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Hugo Delsing", "owner_user_id": "434949"},{"body": " You also need to set the  Access-Control-Allow-Methods  header: \n\n  Header set Access-Control-Allow-Methods \"GET, PUT, POST, DELETE\"\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/08/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/08/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "424", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Cross-origin image load denied despite appropriate permission", "parent_id": "14215811", "comment_count": 5, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "monsur", "owner_user_id": "107250"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Descendants will find all nodes with the name that you are looking for regardless of how far down the XML tree that they are. Try experimenting with something like this: \n\n  foreach (XElement element in xDoc.Children(\"rows\"))\n        &123;\n            foreach (XElement childElement in element.Descendants(\"rows\").Elements(\"primitiveValue\"))\n            &123;\n                Values = Values + \",\" + childElement.Value.ToString();\n            &125;\n        &125;\n  \n\n The key is that using Children should only return nodes that are directly below the root element as opposed to searching the entire structure of the XML document for matching elements. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/17/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/17/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "425", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "XML reading repeating child elements with same name as parent c#", "parent_id": "14387100", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jesse Carter", "owner_user_id": "1364771"},{"body": " Agreeing with @HelenNeely and the OP, a clear explanation of the following would be helpful: Is there any way a client can state  \n\n \n \"Ive seen all articles up to [some date]; please only give me articles that have been updated\" or  \n \"Ive seen all articles up to [some GUID]; please only give me articles that have been updated\". \n \n\n As simple as RSS is, this just seem super-obvious, IMO.  (It would be trivial to implement with an optional URL query arg, like \"?since_date=[datetime]\")   \n\n The answers so far saying \"RSS is pull\" or \"RSS is simple\" dont answer the question (because we are contemplating is still \"pull\" and \"simple\".)  And the W3schools link doesnt described such a feature... which may mean \"it doesnt exist\" or \"the W3schools article didnt cover it\". \n\n Im just too stunned to think this concept of \"pull-since\" could be missing from the spec.  So, to paraphrase Helen: does the client have do download the  whole feed  every time? \n\n  UPDATE:  The answer by @Gabriel gave me what I was looking for.  If you are using  feedparser  in Python, you may wish to look at this documentation on the eTag:  http://packages.python.org/feedparser/http-etag.html .  Please \"+1\" on Gabriels answer! \n", "last_activity_date": "01/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/09/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/09/2013", "id": "426", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How does RSS reader know that a feed is updated?", "parent_id": "1975442", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "701435", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Dan H", "owner_user_id": "701435"},{"body": " You could probably use a console app or a forms app but just dont display the form. I tend to point people to the code samples at:  http://vb.net-informations.com/crystal-report/vb.net_crystal_report_export_pdf.htm  \n\n  Imports CrystalDecisions.CrystalReports.Engine\nImports CrystalDecisions.Shared\nPublic Class Form1\n    Dim cryRpt As New ReportDocument\n\n    Private Sub Button1_Click(ByVal sender As System.Object, _\n    ByVal e As System.EventArgs) Handles Button1.Click\n        cryRpt.Load(\"PUT CRYSTAL REPORT PATH HEREE&#39\\\\&#39CrystalReport1.rpt\")\n        CrystalReportViewer1.ReportSource = cryRpt\n        CrystalReportViewer1.Refresh()\n    End Sub\n\n    Private Sub Button2_Click(ByVal sender As System.Object, _\n    ByVal e As System.EventArgs) Handles Button2.Click\n        Try\n            Dim CrExportOptions As ExportOptions\n            Dim CrDiskFileDestinationOptions As New _\n            DiskFileDestinationOptions()\n            Dim CrFormatTypeOptions As New PdfRtfWordFormatOptions()\n            CrDiskFileDestinationOptions.DiskFileName = _\n                                        \"c:E&#39\\\\&#39crystalExport.pdf\"\n            CrExportOptions = cryRpt.ExportOptions\n            With CrExportOptions\n                .ExportDestinationType = ExportDestinationType.DiskFile\n                .ExportFormatType = ExportFormatType.PortableDocFormat\n                .DestinationOptions = CrDiskFileDestinationOptions\n                .FormatOptions = CrFormatTypeOptions\n            End With\n            cryRpt.Export()\n        Catch ex As Exception\n            MsgBox(ex.ToString)\n        End Try\n    End Sub\nEnd Class\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/09/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "427", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Export crystal report into pdf in vb without using form", "parent_id": "14220475", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Lee Tickett", "owner_user_id": "1091061"},{"body": " I have found one other way to do it (not sure that it is the best however). I call the propertyWillChange and propertyDidChange methods: \n\n  var App = Ember.Application.create(&123;\n    ready: function() &123;\n        console.info(\"Preparing the timer...\");\n        setInterval(function() &123;\n            console.info(\"Updating clock (\" + new Date() + \")\");\n            App.theClockController.propertyWillChange(currentTime);\n            App.theClockController.propertyDidChange(currentTime);\n        &125;, 1000)\n    &125;\n&125;);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/09/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "428", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Is it possible to periodically notify observers of a computed property with ember.js?", "parent_id": "14232665", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Olivier Liechti", "owner_user_id": "1341338"},{"body": " Any method of bypassing the security filtering system sounds an awful lot like  malware  to me. \n\n If a user (or, more likely, their IT department) have insisted on security settings set to  neurotic , then thats their call. They will have seen an identical warning when they visit CNN or Google online. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/09/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "429", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Browser prompts to add accepted url when IE security is set to HIGH", "parent_id": "14235556", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Richard A.", "owner_user_id": "1700634"},{"body": " I am programming in Python 2.5 as well and wanted a suitable library. Here is how I did it. \n\n donwloaded the simplejson egg file called  simplejson-2.0.6-py2.5-linux-i686.egg from\n http://pypi.python.org/simple/simplejson/  \n\n installed it using the command : \n\n  sudo python ./ez_setup.py ./simplejson-2.0.6-py2.5-linux-i686.egg  \n\n Then imported the json library into the script file by doing : \n\n  import sys\nsys.path.append(\"/home/coolkid/Android/simplejson/simplejson-2.0.6-py2.5-linux-i686.egg\")\ntry: import simplejson as json\nexcept ImportError: print (\"import error\")\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/09/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/09/2013", "id": "430", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Python 2.5: JSON module", "parent_id": "791561", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "327466", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Srinivas Rao", "owner_user_id": "1964448"},{"body": " You can use it if you use deletegate in your   someFunction  \n\n     someFunction(delegate( int a, int b) &123;\n       // do some stuff\n    &125;);\n  \n\n Here is a   DEMO  . \n", "last_activity_date": "01/10/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/10/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/10/2013", "id": "431", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "C# delegate in function call", "parent_id": "14261737", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "447156", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Soner G\u00f6n\u00fcl", "owner_user_id": "447156"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Well, no one replied, and this works just fine in Safari, so it has to be a Chrome (v23.0) bug. \n\n What I did to work around the ghosting of the drag-dropped divs is to fadeIn/fadeOut the origin div and that seems to take care of it. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/11/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/11/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "432", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Chrome flexbox drag and drop redraw bug?", "parent_id": "14187703", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "GR7", "owner_user_id": "34683"},{"body": " I think this will work, although it would be nice to have sample data to verify: \n\n  SELECT COALESCE(SUM(a.samt), 0) - COALESCE(SUM(b.samt), 0)\n       + COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN ord.stat = 16\n                                AND b.samt &lt; 0\n                           THEN ord.samt END), 0)\nFROM PUB.ord ord\nLEFT JOIN PUB.opn a\n       ON a.subsnum = ord.subsnum\n          AND a.onum = ord.onum\n          AND a.samt &gt;= 0\n          AND ord.stat != 16\nLEFT JOIN PUB.opn b\n          ON b.subsnum = ord.subsnum\n             AND b.onum = ord.onum\n             AND b.samt &lt; 0\n             AND ord.stat = 16\nWHERE ord.DM1 IN(XCWAJC25, WCWAMO73) \n      AND ord.prdcde = CSC\nGROUP BY ord.DM1\n  \n\n Notes on query/stuff:   \n\n \n Always explicitly qualify joins, dont use the comma-separated  FROM  clause \n I dont think you needed  ord.DM1 !=  , given that values have to be in a specific set \n Putting a clause into a  LEFT JOIN  condition instead of the  WHERE  clause has a slightly different effect; it adds the condition to the join, instead of the filtering.  This means that rows can be excluded based on something in the left table, regardless of whether you need the actual row (this is why  ord.stat  ended up in the  LEFT JOIN s).   INNER JOIN s would technically behave the same way, but it isnt usually noticeable because causing the right table to be excluded also excludes the left table. \n \n", "last_activity_date": "01/11/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/11/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "433", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Progress DB, need to merge two queries", "parent_id": "14281930", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Clockwork-Muse", "owner_user_id": "812837"},{"body": " You would use the form action to redirect to a script where you do the update. On this script you can access the the forms input elements by using the $_POST array. As for how to do update queries, an example could be:  \n\n  $query=\"UPDATE mytable \n        SET title = \".$title.\", name = \".$name.\", date = \".$date.\" \n        WHERE id = \".$id;\n$result=mysql_query($query);\n  \n\n UPDATE: \n\n An example of the script could be: \n\n  $hometeam_position = $_POST[hometeam_position]; //access the selected option when submitting\n$countdown_module = $_POST[countdown_module]; //access the text input\n\n$query = \"UPDATE jos_gm_nextmatch SET countdown_module = \".$countdown_module.\", hometeam_position = \".$hometeam_position.\" WHERE id = 1\";\n$result=mysql_query($query);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/12/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/12/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/12/2013", "id": "434", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to update values in my DB with new values from &lt;select&gt; and &lt;input&gt; tags?", "parent_id": "14296916", "comment_count": 3, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1072372", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "cnh1991", "owner_user_id": "1072372"},{"body": " I think it is because of name miss match.\nThe name which is declare in @NamedQuery in not match with the name which is called that query. \n\n e.g \n\n  @NamedQuery(name = \"AAAA\", query = ... ) //must be same the name which call that query\n\npublic void some() &123;\n   Query q = em.createNamedQuery(\"AAAA\");\n &125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/13/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/13/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "435", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Named query not found.(Entity Manager not creating NamedQuery)", "parent_id": "14152582", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "9ine", "owner_user_id": "1516597"},{"body": " you can find here a good configuration of a spring 3.2 project with maven, \n\n  https://github.com/andonescu/springmvc-freemarker  \n\n and use maven to download source code, see this link to help you \n Maven \u2013 Always download sources and javadocs  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/16/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/16/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "436", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Where can I find spring3.1 aspect Java source code. Seem to be nowhere in github or anywhere else", "parent_id": "14351368", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ionut", "owner_user_id": "543114"},{"body": " I think you have to check for different screen size in your activity and then use appropriate xml for that. following code may work \n\n  DisplayMetrics dm = new DisplayMetrics();\n    getWindowManager().getDefaultDisplay().getMetrics(dm);\n    final int height=dm.heightPixels;\n    final int width=dm.widthPixels;\n\n    if(width == 720 || width==1280 &amp;&amp; height == 1280 || height==720)    //galaxy s3\n    &123;\n      //code to select xml file\n    &125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/16/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/16/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "437", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How can I use different codes for different screen sizes?", "parent_id": "14357744", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Sumedh Tambat", "owner_user_id": "1308410"},{"body": " You might be able to get away with using reflection to set the LocalReport on a ReportViewer but be warned that this could cause issues.  Im doing this on a project right now and it seems to work well.  See my answer here:  http://stackoverflow.com/a/14329386/285874  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/16/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/16/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "438", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "VS2010 RDLC C#. How can I set a LocalReport object to a ReportViewer?", "parent_id": "9200308", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Discofunk", "owner_user_id": "285874"},{"body": " using  ?strptime  \n\n  tt &lt;- getQuote(\"AAPL\")\ntt[,1]\n[1] \"01/16/2013 02:52:00 CET\"\nas.POSIXct(strptime(tt[,1],format =%Y-%m-%d)) ## as.POSIXct because strptime returns POSIXlt\n[1] \"01/16/2013 CET\"\n  \n\n  EDIT  \n\n You can use the format argument of POSIXct, but you need to convert the tt[,1] to character before. \n\n  as.POSIXct(as.character(tt[,1]),format =%Y-%m-%d)\n[1] \"01/16/2013 CET\"\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/16/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/16/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/16/2013", "id": "439", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "extract part of a date in a dataframe column", "parent_id": "14366688", "comment_count": 7, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "1838509", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "agstudy", "owner_user_id": "1838509"},{"body": " Its generally bad for an application (mobile, web, any client) to directly have access to any database for security issues. Clients really should not be accessing the database, which is often holding very private/secure data. It opens up vulnerabilities (i.e., sql injection attack). \n\n A set of web services written in php or java or some back-end technology is a more secure, scalable system. These web services can connect to the database and retrieve data. Your iOS application can call the web services and receive the data..for example in the form of XML or JSON. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/17/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/17/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "440", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "the reason not to access directly from xcode to mssql?", "parent_id": "14374501", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Rohan Agarwal", "owner_user_id": "1508642"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Thanks Aurand for giving me the idea of injecting mock object into application class. Using @InjectMock works fine.  \n\n  @MOCK\nPaymentBusinessService paymentBusinessService;\n\n@InjectMock\nApplication application = PluginSystem.INSTANCE.getPluginInjector().getInstance(Application.class);  \n@Test(enabled = true)// Test Class\npublic void testReCalculatePrepaids() throws Exception &123;\n//Mocking External Call\nwhen(paymentBusinessService.checkForCreditCardReport(this.deal.getId())).thenReturn(new       String(\"Decline by only Me\"));\nString report = paymentBusinessService.checkForCreditCardReport(this.deal.getId());\n//Calling Impl Class whose one external call is mocked\nApplication sc = BusinessService.applicationValidation(this.deal);  \n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/17/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/17/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/17/2013", "id": "441", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How do I mock external method call with Mockito", "parent_id": "14269502", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1968389", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "jan", "owner_user_id": "1968389"},{"body": " Best way I can think of is that you check that all four corners of the form are on a screen.  Like this: \n\n      public bool FormOnScreen(Form frm) &123;\n        if (frm.IsHandleCreated) throw new InvalidOperationException();\n        if (!frm.Visible || frm.WindowState == FormWindowState.Minimized) return false;\n        return PointVisible(new Point(frm.Left, frm.Top)) &amp;&amp;\n               PointVisible(new Point(frm.Right, frm.Top)) &amp;&amp;\n               PointVisible(new Point(frm.Right, frm.Bottom)) &amp;&amp;\n               PointVisible(new Point(frm.Left, frm.Bottom));\n    &125;\n\n    private static bool PointVisible(Point p) &123;\n        var scr = Screen.FromPoint(p);\n        return scr.Bounds.Contains(p);\n    &125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/17/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/17/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "442", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Check if Form is in bounds of all screens", "parent_id": "14383514", "comment_count": 3, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Hans Passant", "owner_user_id": "17034"},{"body": " When contols visibility is in  Collapsed  state its margins do not participate in the layout (contrary to  Hidden  state) \n\n Can be verified easily: \n\n  &lt;Window x:Class=\"MarginsRespectForCollapsedTest.MainWindow\"\n        xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation\"\n        xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml\"\n        Title=\"MainWindow\" Height=\"350\" Width=\"525\"&gt;\n    &lt;StackPanel&gt;\n        &lt;Button Margin=\"50,50\" Visibility=\"Collapsed\"&gt;Im Collapsed&lt;/Button&gt;\n        &lt;Button&gt;Im Visible!&lt;/Button&gt;\n    &lt;/StackPanel&gt;\n&lt;/Window&gt;\n  \n\n I agree with HighCore that you XAML really looks like you just dragged controls from the toolbox panel. VSs XAML designer has this unpleasant feature: it tries to position controls with the help of margins. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/17/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/17/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "443", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "System.Windows.Visibility Collapsed vs Hidden", "parent_id": "14388777", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "voroninp", "owner_user_id": "921054"},{"body": " You can use ValidationMessageFor to apply a custom message if you want a different message to one pre defined in an attribute \n\n  @Html.ValidationMessageFor(m =&gt; m.OwnerBirthDate, \"custom error message\")\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/18/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/18/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "444", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "MVC3 How to define custom error messages using annotations?", "parent_id": "14397098", "comment_count": 4, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "NinjaNye", "owner_user_id": "611288"},{"body": " I dont see the  complexity ... If you need to construct efficiently based on an if-condition declaring a pointer and using new is your only option. What you dont necessarily need to do is: \n\n \n Use a scoped_ptr (altough thats usually a good idea) \n Have the constructor in the if in your \"main\" code. Yours is a typical use case for a factory (see e.g.  http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factory_method_pattern ). \n \n\n EDIT: added \"efficiently\" in the second sentence. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/19/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/18/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/19/2013", "id": "445", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Selecting between two constructors", "parent_id": "14404904", "comment_count": 6, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "1368103", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Epikuros", "owner_user_id": "1368103"},{"body": " your code should be like this. \n\n  public class MainActivity extends Activity implements OnClickListener&123;\n\n\n@Override\nprotected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) &123;\n    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);\n    setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);\n\nButton button = (Button)findViewById(R.id.button1);\nbutton.setOnClickListener(this);  &lt;&lt;ERROR HERE\n&125;\n\n@Override\npublic boolean onCreateOptionsMenu(Menu menu) &123;\n    // Inflate the menu; this adds items to the action bar if it is present.\n    getMenuInflater().inflate(R.menu.activity_main, menu);\n    return true;\n&125;\n\n@Override\npublic void onClick(View arg0) &123;\n    TextView text = (TextView)findViewById(R.id.textmessage);\n    text.setText(\"BUTTON HAS BEEN CLICKED. EVENT PROCESSED.\");\n\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/22/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/22/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "446", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Syntax error setOnClickListener", "parent_id": "14451760", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Raj", "owner_user_id": "1545195"},{"body": " You can use NSCache for this  \n\n   [cache setObject:yourcellcontaint forKey:someKey];  \n  \n\n And get it where you want: \n\n  [cache objectForKey:someKey]\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/22/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/22/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "447", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Best Way to Save a Recent list for uitableView", "parent_id": "14456862", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "V-Xtreme", "owner_user_id": "1352747"},{"body": " If you want to update your listView from another class you can have a few ways to do that. \n\n \n  Send broadcastIntent from your worker class and add BroadcastReceiver to your activity and when you receive the right message, update your listview.  \n  Second way is to create private or public class in your Activity which extends  AsyncTask  and in your  doInBackground()  do your work and in  onPostExecute(result)  update your listview.  \n  Third way which I can imagine, but I dont think its the best way create a static method is your activity which you can use from any other class for updatiogn your UI.  \n \n\n The best thing which you can use here at least in my opinion is  AsyncTask . \n", "last_activity_date": "04/18/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/24/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "04/18/2013", "id": "448", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Updating UI of Android activity from some other class running on different thread", "parent_id": "14499289", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "928814", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Android-Developer", "owner_user_id": "1511776"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Today I had the same problem and worked alot for the solution. I try to show what I did here also for others. \n\n The main problem is (as you said), that the change event isnt triggerd correctly. Also not if you type something like element.change(). \n\n So I found this method: \n\n      function fireEvent(element,event)\n&123;\n    if (document.createEventObject)\n    &123;\n        // dispatch for IE\n        var evt = document.createEventObject();\n        return element.fireEvent(on+event,evt);\n    &125;\n    else\n    &123;\n        // dispatch for firefox + others\n        var evt = document.createEvent(\"HTMLEvents\");\n        evt.initEvent(event, true, true );\n        return !element.dispatchEvent(evt);\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n from  http://icebergcommerce.com/software/blog/iss/article/magento-configurable-products-setting-default-value-for-options/  \n\n Then I triggered the change method over: \n\n      var obj = jQuery(#+parentObj.attr(value)).get();\n    Event.observe(obj[0],change,function()&123;&125;);\n    fireEvent(obj[0],change);\n  \n\n Hereby is obj the normal JS Select Object from the dropdown. \n\n I hope it helps ! \n", "last_activity_date": "01/22/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/22/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "449", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "remotely manipulating the configurable products select dropdown menus", "parent_id": "14306994", "comment_count": 1, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Manuel Gruschka", "owner_user_id": "2000183"},{"body": " That line is fine.  Try looking around it. \n", "last_activity_date": "09/19/2011", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "09/19/2011", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "450", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "What&#39s wrong with UIColor *clr = [UIColor colorWithRed:1.0 green:1.0 blue:1.0 alpha:1.0];?", "parent_id": "7464446", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "IshaanGandhi", "owner_user_id": "790102"},{"body": " The difference is that the first example is  semantically marked up , assuming the data being marked up is not actually tabular.  &lt;table&gt;  should only be used for  tabular data , not for any data which happens to be displayed in a layout similar to a table. \n\n It is correct though that using CSS packages like Bootstrap, which require you to assign classes to HTML elements which are  not  semantic but presentational, reduces the separation of content and presentation, making the difference somewhat moot. You  should  be assigning semantically meaningful classes to your elements and use lesscss mixins (or similar technology) to assign presentational behavior defined in the CSS framework to these classes, instead of assigning the presentational classes to the elements directly. \n\n Say: \n\n  &lt;div class=\"products\"&gt;\n    &lt;div class=\"product\"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n\n.products &123;\n    .row;\n&125;\n\n.products &gt; .product &123;\n    .span16;\n&125;\n  \n\n Note that I say  should . In practice this is not necessarily always the more workable option, but it should be the theoretical goal. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/22/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/22/2013", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "01/22/2013", "id": "451", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Why is the Bootstrap grid layout preferable to an HTML table?", "parent_id": "14461103", "comment_count": 6, "score": 5, "last_editor_user_id": "476", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "deceze", "owner_user_id": "476"},{"body": " You can create multiple TOCs in RoboHelp, but you can only output one at a time.  In other words, each compiled Help can only contain one TOC.  But you can create multiple Helps, each with different TOCs and then you just have to tell your Java code which Help you want to open.    \n\n \n Create one  Single Source Layout  for each TOC you want to produce. \n Specify which TOC you want to use in each  Single Source Layout  ( Single Source Layout  > >   Content  settings). \n Generate each  Single Source Layout  to different folders ( Single Source Layout  > >   General  > >   Output Location  settings). \n Tell Java which Help to launch based on your own critera. \n \n", "last_activity_date": "01/23/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/23/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "452", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Creating Multiple TOC for my ROBOHELP", "parent_id": "13797970", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Hobbleknee", "owner_user_id": "1427952"},{"body": " You can not use the entityManager in your constructor. As injections has not yet happend then \n\n instead move this code to a method annotated @PostConstruct \n\n  @PostConstruct\npublic init() &123;\n\n    Query q = em.createQuery(\"select d.dName from District d\",District.class);\n    districtValues = q.getResultList();\n\n    for(String d:districtValues)&123;\n        System.out.println(d);\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n Method annotated @PostConstruct will be invoked after your EM and EJBs has been injected. \n\n A tip when learning about dependency injections is to keep the examples really small and just get basic end-to-end functionality to work. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/23/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/23/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "453", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "JSF selectonemenu can&#39;t instantiate class", "parent_id": "14478186", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Aksel Willgert", "owner_user_id": "1418643"},{"body": " There are two pobable mistakes. \n\n 1 - Probable the variable are $results and not $result\n2 - If you are using foreach, you dont need the [0], because this is the variable $value now. \n\n try \n\n  foreach ($results as $value) &123;\n    echo $value-&gt;message; \n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/23/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/23/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "454", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "php reading value from an array", "parent_id": "14485734", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Gabriel Lucas", "owner_user_id": "1082199"},{"body": " Apparently Icecast does a lot of what youre looking for. Its open source (GPL) and supports Opus streams using the Ogg container format, you could have a peek for some general software architecture ideas. My SoundWire Android app (with Win/Linux server) does Opus streaming with low latency but the network protocols are custom... I dont know any established open protocols that can do low latency (by my definition 1 second delay is not low latency). \n\n My approach was to build a conventional network server that sets up a normal unicast UDP socket for each client. Avoid TCP if you want low latency, then youll have to deal with the datagram nature of UDP in some way. With Opus the amount of data streamed per client is not excessive. I use multicast only for discovery (auto locate a server). \n\n I suggest you start with some open source server code and adapt it for your needs, bring in Opus which is very easy to integrate, choose a container format such as Ogg if its suitable (search for Ogg Opus). If you want browser compatibility then youll more or less be implementing part of a web server (HTTP etc.) and will have to give up on your low latency goals. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/24/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/24/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "455", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Creating an OPUS codec based multicast server (android/linux)", "parent_id": "14324825", "comment_count": 2, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Georgie", "owner_user_id": "1287459"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": "  FileField  accepts a storage parameter. \n\n  https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/models/fields/#django.db.models.FileField.storage  \n\n  from django.core.files.storage import FileSystemStorage\n\nfs = FileSystemStorage(location=/media/photos)\n\nclass Car(models.Model):\n    ...\n    photo = models.FileField(storage=fs)\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/24/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/24/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "456", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "django-storages, how to override back to django&#39;s local file storage", "parent_id": "14506138", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Yuji &#39;Tomita&#39; Tomita", "owner_user_id": "267887"},{"body": " This is a constraint implemented on browsers for security reasons:   Same origin policy   \n\n Safe Workarounds exist: \n\n \n  JSON to JSONP: Bypass Same-Origin Policy  \n Using headers:  Content Security Policy 1.1  \n  YQL  ?! \n \n", "last_activity_date": "01/25/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/25/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/25/2013", "id": "457", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Accessing elements in the iframe", "parent_id": "14514044", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "358906", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Nabil Kadimi", "owner_user_id": "358906"},{"body": " Method  TryUpdateModel  of  Controller  class make it work. However, this way is not pretty elegant. \n\n  ...\npublic ActionResult Save(FormCollection collection)\n        &123;\n            SomethingBase model = null;\n            if (collection.AllKeys.Contains(\"SpecificOne\"))\n            &123;\n                model = new ChildOne();\n                TryUpdateModel&lt;ChildOne&gt;((ChildOne)model, collection);\n            &125;\n            else\n            &123;\n                model = new ChildTwo();\n                TryUpdateModel&lt;ChildTwo&gt;((ChildTwo)model, collection);\n            &125;\n...\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/25/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/25/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "458", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Inheritance in action method parameters", "parent_id": "14519252", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "xwrs", "owner_user_id": "801306"},{"body": " Its usually better to place your custom CSS after the Bootstrap CSS. Id imagine that youre wanting the custom CSS to override the Bootstrap CSS.  \n\n The advantages of placing your custom styles after Bootstraps is that you can change anything that is set in Bootstraps CSS by using the same selectors that they do. Making it very easy to change minor things. If you use the same selector then the browser will use the last rules applied to an element.  \n\n I cant really see any advantages of placing the Bootstrap CSS after your custom CSS, it wouldnt really make much sense to write your own styles and then override them with Bootstraps... \n\n For example, this isnt bootstrap CSS, but it would work the same way, if you had the following in your head section: \n\n  &lt;link href=\"framework.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /&gt;\n&lt;link href=\"custom-styles.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" /&gt;\n  \n\n Then in  framework.css  you had the following: \n\n  div.row &123;\n    border: 1px solid #eee;\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    margin-bottom: 50px;\n    padding: 15px;\n&125;\n  \n\n But then you realised you wanted to add a red background (why oh why...) and change the border radius, you could have the following in  custom-styles.css : \n\n  div.row &123;\n    background-color: red;\n    border-radius: 10px;\n&125;\n  \n\n The resulting CSS applied to the element would be this: \n\n  div.row &123;\n    background-color: red;\n    border: 1px solid #eee;\n    border-radius: 10px;\n    margin-bottom: 50px;\n    padding: 15px;\n&125;\n  \n\n Because the styles from  custom-styles.css  override the existing ones in  framework.css  and the additional ones are applied too! :) \n", "last_activity_date": "01/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/31/2013", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "01/31/2013", "id": "459", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Twitter Bootstrap Custom CSS inclusion", "parent_id": "14623441", "comment_count": 3, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "1185534", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Seer", "owner_user_id": "1185534"},{"body": " Try this \n\n   JS CODE   \n\n  $(document).ready(function () &123;\n    setInterval(intervalTest, 1000);\n&125;);\n\nfunction intervalTest() &123;\n    $(\"#slide1\").fadeIn(2000, function () &123;\n        $(\"#slide1\").delay(4000).fadeOut(2000);\n        $(\"#slide2\").delay(6000).fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n            $(\"#slide3\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                $(\"#slide4\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                    $(\"#slide5\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                        $(\"#slide6\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                            $(\"#slide7\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                                $(\"#slide8\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                                    $(\"#slide9\").fadeIn(1000, function () &123;\n                                        $(\"div\").delay(2000).fadeOut(1000, function () &123;&125;);\n                                    &125;);\n                                &125;);\n                            &125;);\n                        &125;);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/25/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/25/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "460", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "jQuery looping animation from the beginning", "parent_id": "14528109", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Codegiant", "owner_user_id": "1335954"},{"body": " You need to put the last command in the callback of load() and also the new value of #username must be passed as argument in val() like this \n\n  var user = user_id;\n\njQuery.ajax(&123;\n    type: \"POST\",\n    async : false,\n    url: \"/op/controller.php\",\n    data: &123; method: \"editUser\", user_id: user &125;,\n    contentType : (application/x-www-form-urlencoded),\n    dataType : \"json\" ,\n    success : function(json)&123;\n        $(#lightbox-background).fadeIn(300); \n        $(#lightbox-panel).fadeIn(300).load(forms/editUserForm.php, function()&123;\n           $(#username).val(json.username);\n        &125;);\n    &125;\n&125;);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/26/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/26/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "461", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Fill the fields of lightbox&#39;s form with json data", "parent_id": "14503305", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Tsipizidis Charalampos", "owner_user_id": "1156162"},{"body": " For some font family and font size combinations, a bold \u201c _ \u201d character may look very similar to, or identical with, a regular \u201c _ \u201d character. For example, in 10px Arial, the renderings appear to be identical. For Arial Unicode MS, the difference is small or nonexistent even in default font size or larger; this may relate to the fact that Arial Unicode MS has no bold typeface, so browsers apply algorithmic bolding. Such bolding does not affect horizontal strokes much in general, as you can see by bolding characters like \u201c=\u201d or \u201cH\u201d. \n\n There can be differences between browsers due to different font rendering technologies. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/28/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/28/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "462", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "HTML/CSS - Bold underscore character", "parent_id": "14555687", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jukka K. Korpela", "owner_user_id": "1084437"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " So thanks to a couple of threads over on the  dojo-interest  mailing list, props to bpayton, Kenneth G. Franqueiro and kitsonk, I was able to solve this problem. \n\n In order to get dojo/request to work you need to require it from a module, in this case Ive called it helloworld.js as it is requesting a doc called helloworld.txt: \n\n  // Following taken from:\n// http://dojotoolkit.org/documentation/tutorials/1.8/ajax/\n\nrequire([\"dojo/request\"], function(request)&123;\n    request(\"helloworld.txt\").then(\n        function(text)&123;\n            console.log(\"The files contents is: \" + text);\n        &125;,\n        function(error)&123;\n            console.log(\"An error occurred: \" + error);\n        &125;\n    );\n&125;);\n  \n\n And then include this module in your dojoConfig deps array: \n\n  // dojo-release-1.8.3-src is installed in the same directory as this script\n\ndojoConfig = &123;\n    baseUrl: \".\",\n    packages:[&123;name: dojo, location: dojo&125;],\n    deps:[dojo/request, dojo/date, helloworld.js]\n&125;;\n\nrequire(./dojo/dojo.js);\n\nconsole.log(\"I can call dojo/date functions no problem:\");\nconsole.log(\"e.g. Time Zone is:\" + dojo.date.getTimezoneName(new Date()));\n\nconsole.log(\"And now when I try to use dojo/request it works:\");\n  \n\n Running it from node now gives me: \n\n  arnosgrove:example chris$ node useRequest.js \nI can call dojo/date functions no problem:\ne.g. Time Zone is:GMT\nAnd now when I try to use dojo/request it works\nThe files contents is: &lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//IETF//DTD HTML 2.0//EN\"&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;\n&lt;title&gt;400 Bad Request&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;h1&gt;Bad Request&lt;/h1&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Your browser sent a request that this server could not understand.&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;\n  \n\n Which is what Id expect to see. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/29/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/29/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "463", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Using dojo 1.8 dojo/request under node.js fails with TypeError: Object has no method &#39;substring&#39;", "parent_id": "14584597", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/29/2013", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "worldofchris", "owner_user_id": "1064619"},{"body": " Expanding on an earlier comment: \n\n Many compilers will but the debug and release versions of the executable in different directories. If  file.open(\"templog.txt\");  works in release mode but not in debug mode, thats likely because the input file is located in the same directory as that version of the executable. \n\n To make sure that you always find the file, use a full path name when calling the  open()  function. \n", "last_activity_date": "04/05/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/05/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "464", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "ifstream sets failbit when trying to read a textfile", "parent_id": "15834041", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Bo Persson", "owner_user_id": "597607"},{"body": " You cant call  std::string::operator+  on int types, use  std::stringstream  \n\n  #include &lt;sstream&gt;\n#include &lt;string&gt;\n\nstd::stringstream ss;\nss &lt;&lt; \"&123;symbol = \" &lt;&lt; symbol &lt;&lt; \", qty = \" &lt;&lt; qty &lt;&lt; \", price = \" &lt;&lt; price &lt;&lt; \"&125;\";\n\nstd::string s = ss.str();\n  \n\n Or use  std::to_string  if you use C++11 and boost::lexical_cast to cast integer types to string first: \n\n  std::string s = \"&123;symbol = \" + symbol + \", qty = \" + std::to_string(qty) \n                + \", price = \" + std::to_string(price) + \"&125;\";\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/31/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/31/2013", "id": "465", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Having trouble with adding strings... (c++)", "parent_id": "14618428", "comment_count": 2, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "951757", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "billz", "owner_user_id": "951757"},{"body": " I used  http://stackoverflow.com/a/3431104/2022534  but replaced Djangos model_to_dict() with this to be able to handle ForeignKey: \n\n  def model_to_dict(instance):\n    data = &123;&125;\n    for field in instance._meta.fields:\n        data[field.name] = field.value_from_object(instance)\n        if isinstance(field, ForeignKey):\n            data[field.name] = field.rel.to.objects.get(pk=data[field.name])\n    return data\n  \n\n Please note that I have simplified it quite a bit by removing the parts of the original I didnt need. You might want to put those back. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/31/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "466", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Django - Iterate over model instance field names and values in template", "parent_id": "2170228", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Magnus Gustavsson", "owner_user_id": "2022534"},{"body": " \n   do I need to use the return function to let it continue looping \n \n\n You dont need a return to continue to loop. You use  return  when you want to return from the current function and go back. \n\n \n   If called from within a function, the return statement immediately\n  ends execution of the current function, and returns its argument as\n  the value of the function call. return will also end the execution of\n  an eval() statement or script file. \n \n\n PHP &amp; Query \n\n  while($qtytoAdd &gt; 0) &123;\n    if(($remBalance - $qtytoAdd) &gt;= 0) &123;\n        mysql_query(UPDATE `estimates` SET `qty_rec` = `qty_rec` + \".$qtytoAdd.\" WHERE `proj_id` = \".$proj_id.\" AND `mat_id` = \".mat_id_from_mat_desc($materials).\" AND `est_id` = \".$balid.\");\n        mysql_query(UPDATE `requestdetails` SET `current_rec_qty` = `current_rec_qty` + \".$qtytoAdd.\" WHERE `proj_id` = \".$proj_id.\" AND `mat_id` = \".mat_id_from_mat_desc($materials).\" AND `req_id` = \".$currid.\");\n        $qtytoAdd = $qtytoAdd - $remBalance; // this part does not exist in your code.\n        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^-------- depends on your requirement. I added the same line.  \n &125; else &123;\n        mysql_query(UPDATE `estimates` SET `qty_rec` = \".$remBalance.\" + \".$currRec.\" WHERE `proj_id` = \".$proj_id.\" AND `mat_id` = \".mat_id_from_mat_desc($materials).\" AND `est_id` = \".$balid.\");\n        mysql_query(UPDATE `requestdetails` SET `current_rec_qty` = \".$remBalance.\" + \".$currRec.\" WHERE `proj_id` = \".$proj_id.\" AND `mat_id` = \".mat_id_from_mat_desc($materials).\" AND `req_id` = \".$currid.\");\n        $qtytoAdd = $qtytoAdd - $remBalance;\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n Where you have gone wrong  \n\n According to your code if the 1st if is true you dont make changes to the $qtytoAdd. Plus you return from the function. So the while loop will be executed only once. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/31/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "467", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "query inside a while loop", "parent_id": "14629337", "comment_count": 3, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Dasun", "owner_user_id": "1263783"},{"body": " The  UISearchDisplayController  cant be hidden or shown - its just the manager for an  UISearchBar .  UISearchBar  inherits from  UIView , which is what you want to work with. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/31/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "468", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "UISearchDisplayController does not showing when adding programatically", "parent_id": "14632237", "comment_count": 4, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "SAE", "owner_user_id": "577483"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": "  static &123;\n     // add handlers for main MIME types\n    MailcapCommandMap mcap = new MailcapCommandMap();\n    mcap.addMailcap(\"text/plain;; x-java-content-handler=com.sun.mail.handlers.text_plain\");\n    mcap.addMailcap(\"text/html;; x-java-content-handler=com.sun.mail.handlers.text_html\");\n    mcap.addMailcap(\"text/xml;; x-java-content-handler=com.sun.mail.handlers.text_xml\");\n    mcap.addMailcap(\"multipart/*;; x-java-content-handler=com.sun.mail.handlers.multipart_mixed; x-java-fallback-entry=true\");\n    mcap.addMailcap(\"message/rfc822;; x-java-content-handler=com.sun.mail.handlers.message_rfc822\");\n    CommandMap.setDefaultCommandMap(mcap);\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "02/06/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/06/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "469", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "MessagingExceptionIOException while sending message in java?", "parent_id": "4612673", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "user2047855", "owner_user_id": "2047855"},{"body": "  [01][05]|[4][5]|[3][0]   may match  10  or  05 , you are looking for  [03]0|[14]5 . \n\n  :(...)?  validates strings that end with  : . You want something like  (:...)?  - the colon should be inside the parentheses. \n\n Make sure to escape the dots:  .  and not  .  - otherwise it matches all characters. \n\n If this ends up on the .net engine,  E&#39\\\\&#39d  matches all Unicode digits, so you may prefer  [0-9] . \n\n I would also suggest the following code, which may prove much more robust (for example - it invalidates dates like 29.02.2013 vs 29.02.2012): \n\n  public bool IsValidDateAndHour(string input)\n&123;\n    DateTime date;\n    bool success = DateTime.TryParseExact(input, \"dd.MM.yyyy HH:mm\",\n                                          CultureInfo.InvariantCulture,\n                                          DateTimeStyles.None, out date);\n    return success &amp;&amp; date.Minute % 15 == 0;\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/31/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/31/2013", "id": "470", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Improve Regular Expression to match date time by quarters", "parent_id": "14636274", "comment_count": 2, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "7586", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Kobi", "owner_user_id": "7586"},{"body": " You can define in your styles.xml \n\n      &lt;style name=\"Theme.Base\" parent=\"...\"&gt;\n        &lt;item name=\"activatableItemBackground\"&gt;@drawable/activatable_item_background&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;/style&gt;\n\n   &lt;style name=\"ListItemContainerBase\"&gt;\n        &lt;item name=\"android:background\"&gt;?activatableItemBackground&lt;/item&gt;\n    &lt;/style&gt;\n  \n\n In res/drawable define activatable_item_background.xml \n\n  &lt;selector xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"&gt;\n    &lt;item android:drawable=\"@drawable/item_pressed\" android:state_pressed=\"true\" /&gt;\n    &lt;item android:drawable=\"@drawable/item_focused\" android:state_focused=\"true\" /&gt;\n    &lt;item android:drawable=\"@drawable/item_focused\" android:state_selected=\"true\" /&gt;\n    &lt;item android:drawable=\"@drawable/item_activated\" android:state_activated=\"true\" /&gt;\n    &lt;item android:drawable=\"@drawable/item_checked\" android:state_checked=\"true\" /&gt;\n    &lt;item android:drawable=\"@android:color/transparent\" /&gt;\n&lt;/selector&gt;\n  \n\n item_pressed, item_focused..... are images in res/drawable-xxx \n\n Define for each items in your view a layout like this: \n\n  &lt;FrameLayout xmlns:android=\"http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android\"\n    android:layout_width=\"match_parent\"\n    android:layout_height=\"wrap_content\"\n    style=\"@style/ListItemContainerBase\"&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "02/01/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/01/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "471", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to highlight selected list item in android?", "parent_id": "14645275", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Gabriele Mariotti", "owner_user_id": "2016562"},{"body": " It&#39s because you are appending  l  to  url  on every iteration without initializing  url .  \n\n You should do: \n\n  #....\nurl2 = url + str(l)\nprint url2\n#....\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "06/07/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "06/07/2012", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "472", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Unexpected python loop output", "parent_id": "10938971", "comment_count": 1, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "wroniasty", "owner_user_id": "239545"},{"body": " You are not invoking  selector , just comparing the  instance  of the expression.  The correct way should be \n\n  static IEnumerable&lt;T&gt; Order&lt;T&gt;(IEnumerable&lt;T&gt; enumerables, bool ascending)\n&123;\n    Func&lt;T, object&gt; selector = (z) =&gt; z;\n    if (ascending)\n        return enumerables.OrderBy(z =&gt; selector(z));\n    else\n        return enumerables.OrderByDescending(z =&gt; selector(z));\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "02/01/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/01/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "473", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Assigning a lambda expression causes it to not be executed later?", "parent_id": "14655639", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "I4V", "owner_user_id": "1906557"},{"body": " To open file from the jar resources see:  Class#getResourceAsStream . \n\n Code example to read text file: \n\n      try &123;\n        InputStream in = getClass().getResourceAsStream(\"resource name\"); // get binary stream to resource\n        // InputStream in = new FileInputStream(\"filePath\"); //in case file loaded from the FileSystem\n        BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(in));\n        String line = null;\n        while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null)\n        &123;\n            if (line.startsWith(\"add\")) &123;\n                // e.t.c.\n            &125;\n        &125;\n    &125;\n    catch (IOException e) &123;\n        //process exception or throw up\n    &125;\n  \n\n \n\n It is easier to load file from resources using  Guava : \n\n  URL url = Resources.getResource(resourceName);\nList&lt;String&gt; text = Resources.readLines(url, Charsets.UTF_8);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "02/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/03/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "474", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Reading files inside a jar?", "parent_id": "14669673", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Taky", "owner_user_id": "1554314"},{"body": "  iqsort  actually looks fully general to me. If you look at the Data.Vector.Generic haddocks, you in fact can use that interface for  any   a ! The difference is that the function as given is  more  generic, because it allows you to choose an  unboxed  vector, which of course only works over  some   a . \n\n Heres the link:  http://hackage.haskell.org/packages/archive/vector/0.10.0.1/doc/html/Data-Vector-Generic.html  \n\n So if you pick your V to be boxed, the vector constraint goes away. \n", "last_activity_date": "02/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/03/2013", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "475", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Is it possible to implement a general in-place quicksort in haskell?", "parent_id": "14675646", "comment_count": 4, "score": 5, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "sclv", "owner_user_id": "371753"},{"body": " See  here  and  here .  mysqli_stmt::execute()  by default stores the results server side and fetches row by row unless you call  mysqli_stmt::store_result()  to buffer them client side. Attempting to prepare another statement most likely fails while there are unfetched reults server side from a previous statement. \n", "last_activity_date": "02/06/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/06/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "476", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Call to a member function bind_param() on a non-object not working inside function called from another function", "parent_id": "14718620", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "bmused", "