curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " The similar question has been asked before follow this  link  hope it may help you. \n\n Basic flow is like this. \n\n  # clone the repository (from github, for example)\ngit clone git@github.com:username/reponame.git\ncd reponame    \n\n# edit some files\n\n# add them to the index\ngit add file1.txt\ngit add file2.gif\n\n# review your changes\ngit status    \n\n# commit the changes\ngit commit -m \"Decription of my change\"\n\n# push them back to the remote repository\ngit push origin master\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/07/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "534", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to take update from github repository?", "parent_id": "15264119", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Janmejoy", "owner_user_id": "1566194"},{"body": " You should be able to add a hidden  input  field with the name of the  MERGE TAG  set for the specific group.  \n\n However, for this functionality it would be much easier to utilize the  MailChimp API  (even though your question suggests youd rather not).  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/03/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "535", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Mailchimp: Add subscriber to group with signup form, not API", "parent_id": "14717248", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "adamdehaven", "owner_user_id": "1245596"},{"body": " Modify the while loop to be a do.. while loop \n\n @ashrafi iqbal \n\n  do\n&123;\n    if(*q== )\n    &123;\n        r=q+1;\n        while(r!=s+1)\n        &123;\n        printf(\"%c\",*r);\n        r++;\n        &125;\n        printf(\" \",*r);\n        s=q-1;\n    &125;\n    q--;\n&125;while(q!=str);\n  \n\n    ___  EDIT   _ _  \n\n modify if condition as  \n\n  if ((*q== ) || (*q == str[strlen(str) - 1))\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/07/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "03/07/2013", "id": "536", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Code for reversing a string word by word is given below. Put a condition in while loop so that following program starts working completely", "parent_id": "15264708", "comment_count": 8, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "2135710", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "hazzelnuttie", "owner_user_id": "2135710"},{"body": " Theres a few things to change to make it work. \n\n First, your  MyObjectPanel  class needs to have a  MyObject  variable and return that instead of a new one each time  getMyObject  is called. This variable is set when  setMyObject  is called on  MyObjectPanel . \n\n  // End of variables declaration\n\nprivate MyObject object;\nvoid setMyObject(MyObject myObject) &123;\n  object = myObject;\n...\n&125;\n\nMyObject getMyObject() &123;\n  return object;\n&125;\n  \n\n Second, your  MyObject  class needs a  int row  variable to be able to know which row it represents. Make a getter too for this variable. Set this variable in the  for  loop in  createGUI  . \n\n Last, in the  while  of your  ProgressRunnable  in  run , you need to stop editing the cell if thats the one your progress is running. To do that, you check with  JTable.getEditingRow , if the table  isEditing  that this row is the same as  myObject.getRow  that the progress  myObject  variable. Something like this : \n\n  myObject.setProgress(progress);\n          if (table.isEditing()) &123;\n            if (table.getEditingRow() == myObject.getRow()) &123;\n              table.getCellEditor().stopCellEditing();\n            &125;\n          &125;\n          model.fireTableRowsUpdated(row, row);\n  \n\n Also note that I changed the  setValue  there for  fireTableRowsUpdated  instead. \n\n This should make it work as you want. \n\n You can remove your  TableModelListener  in  createGUI  and only call  setPreferredRowHeights  once before  pack . \n", "last_activity_date": "03/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/07/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "537", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "ProgressBar inside JTable", "parent_id": "15278268", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jonathan Drapeau", "owner_user_id": "773623"},{"body": " Your  UserDao  object needs to come from the Spring object store as well as your mapper. Instantiating the UserDao object inside of your  index  method like you do will mean the mapper is  null  when you make your call, since Spring didnt set the object up for you and thus cant autowire your mapper. \n\n You will want to use an  @Resource  annotation to bring your UserDao object into your Controller, like below: \n\n   @Controller\n @RequestMapping(\"/authenticate\")\n public class LoginController &123;\n\n    @Resource\n    UserDao userDao;\n\n    @RequestMapping(\"/index\")\n    public String index() &123;\n        System.out.println(userDao.getUser(1).getPassword());\n        return \"Login\";\n    &125;\n\n &125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/07/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "538", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "MyBatis with Spring - configuration error Null Pointer Exception", "parent_id": "15280734", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Peter Elliott", "owner_user_id": "1904979"},{"body": " Use the below code. \n\n   &lt;%int nc=1; %&gt; \n\n &lt;div id=\"nc&lt;%=nc%&gt;\" class=\"n_content active\"&gt;\n         &lt;!--Some div content--&gt;\n        &lt;%nc++;%&gt;\n &lt;/div&gt;\n &lt;div id=\"nc&lt;%=nc%&gt;\" class=\"n_content\" style=\"opacity: 1;\"&gt;             \n         &lt;!--Some div content--&gt;\n        &lt;%nc++;%&gt;\n &lt;/div&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/04/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "539", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Scriptlet variable in div id", "parent_id": "15804202", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Web_developer", "owner_user_id": "2458820"},{"body": " In the HTML I give the link an ID: \n\n  &lt;div class=\"pauseButton\" style=\"display: block;\"&gt;&lt;a id=\"LinkID\" href=\"#\" address=\"true\"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n  \n\n VB.Net code to get the element by Id and invoke it: \n\n  Private Function ClickSubmitButton()\n\n        Dim theButton As HtmlElement\n\n        Try\n\n             Link the ID from the web form to the Button var\n            theButton = webbrowser1.Document.GetElementById(\"LinkID\")\n\n             Now do the actual click.\n            theButton.InvokeMember(\"click\")\n            Return True\n\n        Catch ex As Exception\n\n            Return False\n\n        End Try\n\n    End Function\n  \n\n Update: \n\n Ok without the LinkID you need to loop through all elements, once you identify the DIV, you know the next element is the link... \n\n  Dim IsRightElement as Boolean = False\nFor Each ele As HtmlElement In wb.Document.Links\n        If IsRightElement Then\n           ele.InvokeMember(\"click\")\n           IsRightElement = False\n           Exit For\n        End If\n        If ele.GetAttribute(\"class\") = \"playButton\" Then\n            IsRightElement = True\n        End If\n    Next\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/08/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/08/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "03/08/2013", "id": "540", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to click links on a webpage in visual basic", "parent_id": "15283960", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "495455", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jeremy Thompson", "owner_user_id": "495455"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " The main benefit of immutability is that an object cannot be changed \"out from under you\".  Eg, consider a String that is a key to a Map.  If it were mutable then one could insert a key/value pair then modify the String that is the key.  This would break the hash scheme used in the map, and lead to some potentially very unpredictable operation. \n\n In some cases such mutability could lead to security exposures, due to intentional abuse, but more commonly it would simply lead to mysterious bugs.  And \"defensive\" copying of the mutable objects (to avoid such bugs) would lead to many more objects being created (especially if a formulaic approach to the problem is taken). \n\n (On the other hand, lots of objects are created, eg, because a new String is created when someone appends to the String, or \"chops off\" a part of it, vs simply mutating the existing String, so both approaches end up causing more objects to be created, for different reasons.) \n", "last_activity_date": "03/10/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/10/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "541", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Why is immutability a desired feature in classes?", "parent_id": "15318445", "comment_count": 0, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Hot Licks", "owner_user_id": "581994"},{"body": " Here is the Solution for you: \n\n  MFMailComposeViewController *mailController = [[MFMailComposeViewController alloc] init];\nmailController.mailComposeDelegate = self;\nNSString *emailBody = @\"&lt;p&gt;Here Your HTML Code&lt;/p&gt;\";                         \n[mailController setMessageBody:emailBody isHTML:YES]; \n[self mailController animated:YES completion:NO];\n  \n\n the implement the delegate \n\n  - (void)mailComposeController:(MFMailComposeViewController *)controller didFinishWithResult:(MFMailComposeResult)result error:(NSError *)error __OSX_AVAILABLE_STARTING(__MAC_NA,__IPHONE_3_0)\n&123;\n// Notifies users about errors associated with the interface\n\nswitch (result)\n\n&123;\n    case MFMailComposeResultCancelled:\n\n        // message.text = @\"Result: canceled\";\n\n        break;\n\n    case MFMailComposeResultSaved:\n\n        // message.text = @\"Result: saved\";\n\n        break;\n\n    case MFMailComposeResultSent:\n\n        //   message.text = @\"Result: sent\";\n\n        break;\n\n    case MFMailComposeResultFailed:\n\n        // message.text = @\"Result: failed\";\n\n        break;\n\n    default:\n\n        //  message.text = @\"Result: not sent\";\n\n        break;\n\n&125;\n\n[self dismissViewControllerAnimated:YES completion:NO];\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/08/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/08/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "542", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Use MFMailComposeViewController to compose HTML message", "parent_id": "15288978", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Saurabh Singh", "owner_user_id": "2131765"},{"body": " You are fine in theory with this scenario (somewhat). Id define your template separately as your template table should really be that - your template table and separate from your rendered entity, otherwise you are really destroying your template if you are rendering directly to it which is likely why you see the first row disappear as its taken up by your template data. \n\n Simply add this beneath your table: \n\n \n &lt;table&gt;\n    &lt;tbody id=&quot;airlineData&quot;&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n\n  \n\n and change your table body to point to the new table. \n\n \n var tableBody = document.getElementById(\"airlineData\");\n  \n\n Let me know if that works for you. \n", "last_activity_date": "03/08/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/08/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "543", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "First item empty - WinJS.Binding.Template", "parent_id": "15291680", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Adam Tuliper - MSFT", "owner_user_id": "371637"},{"body": " You want to remove the navigator option from controls.  Try adding this to the parameter list:  single.opts = \"controls: [first, previous, play, next, last, loop, speed], delayMin: 0\"  \n\n to get something like: \n\n  saveHTML(pp(), autoplay=FALSE, loop=FALSE, \n         verbose=FALSE, outdir = \"new\", \n         single.opts = \"controls: [first, previous, play, next, last, loop, speed], delayMin: 0\")\n  \n\n The default list includes navigator so were just removing that option.  You can reorder these options too if you want. \n", "last_activity_date": "03/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/09/2013", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "544", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "animation: remove dots keep control panel", "parent_id": "15306136", "comment_count": 2, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Dason", "owner_user_id": "1003565"},{"body": " I dont think you can change the background, as well as I dont think you should. \n\n Id try to open \"maximized\" form with large opaque (or half-transparent) border. \n\n May be  this  will be helpful \n", "last_activity_date": "04/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/04/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "545", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to show the form with the desktop background dimmed?", "parent_id": "15814223", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "evgenyl", "owner_user_id": "398797"},{"body": " You could do the following: \n\n  val groups = List(\"E&#39\\\\&#39\"First PartE&#39\\\\&#39\"\", \"E&#39\\\\&#39\"Another PartE&#39\\\\&#39\"\", \"E&#39\\\\&#39\"Yet another sectionE&#39\\\\&#39\"\")\nval accumulator = List[List[String]]()\nval result = input.split(\"E&#39\\\\&#39n\").foldLeft(accumulator)((acc,e) =&gt; &123;\n  if (groups.contains(e)) &123;\n    // Make new group when we encounter a string matching one of the groups\n    Nil :: acc\n  &125; else &123;\n    // Grab current group and modify it\n    val newHead = e :: acc.head \n    newHead :: acc.tail \n  &125;\n&125;)\n  \n\n Each list in  result  now represent a group. If you want to use regex to find your matches then just replace the  groups.contains(e)  with a match test. There are some subtleties here that might deserve a mention: \n\n \n The algorithm will fail if the input does not start with a heading \n If a heading is present several times each time it is present will generate a new group \n Groups will contain the lines in the input in reverse. \n Empty lines will also be included in the result. \n \n", "last_activity_date": "03/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/09/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "03/09/2013", "id": "546", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "parsing a text file into groups using Scala", "parent_