ted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/22/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "572", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Filling remaining vertical space", "parent_id": "15580356", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Lewis", "owner_user_id": "60147"},{"body": " You can use the   TrimEnd()   method. \n\n  return inputString.TrimEnd(/); // .NET 2 or newer\n  \n\n or \n\n  return inputString.TrimEnd(new char[] &123; / &125;); // legacy\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/25/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/25/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "573", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Remove Traiing Foward Slash using UrlRewritingNet", "parent_id": "15611511", "comment_count": 3, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Nolonar", "owner_user_id": "1169228"},{"body": " SOP should be inside any method. Use a constructor and print it inside the constructor and then call super() in the constructor of  accesssp1  \n\n  class accesssp  &123;\n\npublic int a=56;\nprivate int b=5566;\npublic int c=58766;\n\npublic accesssp()\n\n&123;\nSystem.out.println(b);\n&125;\n\n&125;\n\nclass accesssp1 extends accesssp&123;\n\npublic accesssp1()\n&123;\nsuper();\n&125;\n\n\npublic void accessd()   &123;\n\n\nSystem.out.println(a);\nSystem.out.println(c);\n\n&125;\n\n&125;\npublic class Access_Spf &123;\n\npublic static void main(String[] args) &123;\n\n\naccesssp1 sp1 = new accesssp1();\nsp1.accessd();\n\n&125;\n\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/25/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/25/2013", "votes_count": 0