curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Put simply, dont use a recursive function for this situation, there isnt any need: \n\n  var paths = [image1.jpg, image2.jpg, image3.jpg];\nvar images = [];\nvar loads = [];\n\n/// all complete function, probably should be renamed to something with a \n/// unique namespace unless you are working within your own function scope.\nvar done = function()&123;\n  alert(all loaded);\n&125;\n\nvar loaded = function(e,t)&123;\n  /// fallbacks for old IE\n  e = e||Event; t = e.target||e.srcElement;\n  /// keep a list of the loaded images, you can delete this later if wanted\n  loads.push( t.src );\n  if ( loads.length &gt;= paths.length ) &123;\n    done();\n  &125;\n&125;\n\nvar load = function()&123;\n  var i, l = paths.length, img;\n  for( i=0; i&lt;l; i++ )&123;\n    images.push(img = new Image());\n    img.onload = loaded;\n    img.src = paths[i];\n  &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n In fact, as you are finding, the method you are using currently is quite intensive. Instead, the above version doesnt create a new function for each  onload  listener  (saves memory)  and will trigger off as many concurrent loads as your browser will allow  (rather than waiting for each image load) . \n\n  (the above has been manually typed and not tested, as of yet)  \n\n update \n\n Ah, then it makes more sense as to why you are doing things this way :) In that case then your first approach using the  setTimeout  would probably be the best solution (you should be able to use a timeout of  0 ). There is still room for rearranging things to see if you can avoid that though. The following may get around the problem... \n\n  var paths  = [image1.jpg, image2.jpg, image3.jpg];\nvar images = []; /// will contain the image objects\nvar loads  = []; /// will contain loaded paths\nvar buffer = []; /// temporary buffer\nvar done   = function()&123; alert(all loaded); &125;\n\nvar loaded = function(e,t)&123;\n  e = e||Event; t = e.target||e.srcElement; loads.push( t.src );\n  /// you can do your \"timing/start animation\" calculation here...\n  /// check to see if we are complete\n  if ( loads.length &gt;= paths.length ) &123; done(); &125;\n  /// if not fire off the next image load\n  else &123; next(); &125;\n&125;\n\nvar next = function()&123;\n  /// current will be the next image\n  var current = buffer.shift();\n  /// set the load going for the current image\n  if ( current ) &123; current.img.src = current.path; &125;\n&125;\n\nvar load = function()&123;\n  var i, l = paths.length, img;\n  for( i=0; i&lt;l; i++ )&123;\n    img = new Image();\n    img.onload = loaded;\n    /// build up a list of images and paths to load\n    buffer.push(&123; img: img, path: paths[i] &125;);\n  &125;\n  /// set everything going\n  next();\n&125;\n  \n\n If the above doesnt do it, another way of getting around the issue would be to step through your list of paths, one at a time, and append a string of image markup (that would render off-screen) to the DOM with its own  onload=\"next()\"  handler...  next()  would be responsible for inserting the next image. By doing this it would hand off the triggering of the load and the subsequent load event to outside of your code, and should get around stacking calls. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/13/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/12/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "12/13/2012", "id": "575", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "image loading loop IE7 Stack Overflow at line 0", "parent_id": "13850120", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1490904", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "pebbl", "owner_user_id": "1490904"},{"body": " WinForms have tricky model of events for components (and  DataGridView  is a component). Some events are inherited from  Control  (like  FontChanged ,  ForeColorChanged  etc), but all specific to component events stored in single  EventHandlerList  object, which is inherited from  Component  (btw events from Control also stored there, see update at the end of answer). There is protected  Events  property for that: \n\n  protected EventHandlerList Events\n&123;\n    get\n    &123;\n        if (this.events == null)            \n            this.events = new EventHandlerList(this);            \n        return this.events;\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n And here is the way how event handlers are added for  DataGridView  events: \n\n  public event DataGridViewCellEventHandler CellValueChanged\n&123;\n    add &123; Events.AddHandler(EVENT_DATAGRIDVIEWCELLVALUECHANGED, value); &125;\n    remove &123; Events.RemoveHandler(EVENT_DATAGRIDVIEWCELLVALUECHANGED, value); &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n As you can see, delegate (value) is passed to  EventHandlerList  with some key value. All event handlers are stored there by key. You can think about  EventHandlerList  as a dictionary with objects as keys, and delegates as values. So, here how you can get components events with reflection. First step is getting those keys. As you already noticed, they named as  EVENT_XXX : \n\n  private static readonly object EVENT_DATAGRIDVIEWCELLVALUECHANGED;\nprivate static readonly object EVENT_DATAGRIDVIEWCELLMOUSEUP;\n// etc\n  \n\n So here we go: \n\n  var keys = typeof(DataGridView) // you can use `GetType()` of component object\n   .GetFields(BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Static | BindingFlags.FlattenHierarchy)\n   .Where(f =&gt; f.Name.StartsWith(\"EVENT_\"));\n  \n\n Next, we need our  EventHandlerList : \n\n  var events = typeof(DataGridView) // or GetType()\n          .GetProperty(\"Events\", BindingFlags.Instance | BindingFlags.NonPublic);\n// Could be null, check that\nEventHandlerList handlers = events.GetValue(grid) as EventHandlerList;\n  \n\n And last step, getting list of keys, which have handlers attached: \n\n  var result = keys.Where(f =&gt; handlers[f.GetValue(null)] != null)\n                 .ToList();\n  \n\n That will give you keys. If you need delegates, then simply look in handlers list for them. \n\n UPDATE: Events which inherited from  Control  are also stored in  EventHandlerList , but for some unknown reason their keys have different names, like  EventForeColor . You can use same approach as above to get those keys and check if handlers attached. \n", "last_activity_date": "03/26/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/26/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "03/26/2013", "id": "576", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to check which event are assigned?", "parent_id": "15630943", "comment_count": 3, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "470005", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "lazyberezovsky", "owner_user_id": "470005"},{"body": " You need to use the  psql  program that comes that the PostgreSQL package that you installed instead of the  psql  in the  /usr/bin  directory that is part of the Apple system. \n\n For example, if using  postgres.app , they say in their  documentation : \n\n \n   Mac OS 10.7 ships with an older version of PostgreSQL, which can be\n  started with the following command: \n  \n   $ psql -h localhost PostgreSQL ships with a constellation of useful\n  binaries, like pg_dump or pg_restore, that you will likely want to\n  use. Go ahead and add the /bin directory that ships with Postgres.app\n  to your PATH (preferably in .profile, .bashrc, .zshrc, or the like to\n  make sure this gets set for every Terminal session): \n  \n   PATH=\"/Applications/Postgres.app/Contents/MacOS/bin:$PATH\" \n  Once your\n  path is correctly set up, you should be able to run psql without a\n  host. (If not, check that the correct version is being loaded in the\n  PATH by doing which psql) \n \n\n If using another source of pre-packaged postgresql, its the same thing with different paths. \n", "last_activity_date": "03/26/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/26/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "577", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "postgres: localhost not connecting", "parent_id": "15644845", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Daniel V\u00e9rit\u00e9", "owner_user_id": "238814"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Getting a record given some input  \"A\"  or  \"B\"  is pretty simple: \n\n  alpha_data = [(A, Apple, 14.5), (B, Banana, 23.4)]\n\nuser_input = \"A\"\n\n[rec for rec in alpha_data if rec[0] == user_input]\nOut[4]: [(A, Apple, 14.5)]\n  \n\n But if your goal is to allow users to access those entries using  \"A\" ,  \"B\"  etc., then a  dict  seems like the more sensible solution: \n\n  alpha_dict = &123;\"A\": (\"Apple\", 14.5), \"B\": (\"Banana\", 23.4)&125;\n\nuser_input = \"A\"\n\nalpha_dict[user_input]\nOut[8]: (Apple, 14.5)\n  \n\n Applying these ideas to your actual use case is pretty simple, in your attempt you iterated through the data and tried to find matches in the  portfolio_list  keys, but its easier to iterate through  portfolio_list  and look for matches in the data: \n\n  EXCHANGE_DATA = [(AIA, Auckair, 1.50),\n            (AIR, Airnz, 5.60),\n            (AMP, Amp,3.22), \n            (ANZ, Anzbankgrp, 26.25),\n            (ARG, Argosy, 12.22),\n            (CEN, Contact, 11.22),\n            (CNU, Chorus,3.01),\n            (DIL, Diligent, 5.3),\n            (DNZ, Dnz Property, 2.33),\n            (EBO, Ebos, 1.1)]\n\nportfolio_str=input(\"Please list portfolio: \")\nportfolio_str= portfolio_str.replace( ,)\nportfolio_str= portfolio_str.upper()\nportfolio_list= portfolio_str.split(,)\n  \n\n Enter some user input: \n\n  Please list portfolio: AIA, ARG\n  \n\n Printing code: \n\n  print(&123;:&lt;6&125; &123;:&lt;20&125; &123;:&gt;8&125;.format(Code, Name, Price))\nCode   Name                    Price\n\nfor code in portfolio_list:\n    # This assumes there will only be one record per code\n    rec = [rec for rec in EXCHANGE_DATA if rec[0] == code][0]\n    # The *rec part is using a neat python feature called\n    # tuple unpacking, google it if youre not familiar with it\n    print(&123;:&lt;6&125; &123;:&lt;20&125; &123;:&gt;8.2f&125;.format(*rec))\n  \n\n Output: \n\n  AIA    Auckair                  1.50\nARG    Argosy                  12.22\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/27/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/26/2013", "votes_count": 5, "last_edit_date": "03/27/2013", "id": "578", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Comparing user input with tuple value", "parent_id": "15648092", "comment_count": 7, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "1222578", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Marius", "owner_user_id": "1222578"},{"body": " Based on the file content you described, it sounds like a natural properties file: \n\n  # This is a comment:\nlanecount=10001000\ntime=12:00\ntimex=05:00\nanyword=fhfbjkl\u00f6s\nStopbyte=0x28\n... ...\n  \n\n Use  java.util.Properties , it does all dirty work for you: \n\n  # Write properties to private storage:\nFileOutputStream fos = context.openFileOutput(cfg, Context.MODE_PRIVATE);\nProperties props = new Properties();\nprops.setProperty(\"lanecount\", \"10001000\");\nprops.setProperty(\"time\", \"12:00\");\nprop.store(fos, \"This is a comment\"); // store() is threadsafe\nfos.close();\n\n... ...\n\n# Read properties from private storage: \nFileInputStream fis = context.openFileInput(cfg);\nProperties props = new Properties();\nprops.load(fis); // load() is threadsafe\nfis.close();\nString lanecount = props.getProperty(\"lanecount\");\nString time = props.getProperty(\"time\");\n  \n\n I dont know your requirements, as an alternative, you can load/store your configurations from  SharedPreferences  instead of apps private storage: \n\n  # Write properties to shared preferences:\nSharedPreferences prefs = PreferenceManager.getDefaultSharedPreferences(getBaseContext());\nSharedPreferences.Editor editor = prefs.edit();\neditor.putString(\"lanecount\", \"10001000\");\neditor.putString(\"time\", \"12:00\");\neditor.commit();\n\n... ...\n\n# Read properties from shared preferences:\nSharedPreferences prefs = PreferenceManager.getDefaultSharedPreferences(this);\nString lanecount = prefs.getString(\"lanecount\", \"defauleValue\");\nString time = prefs.getString(\"time\", \"defauleValue\");\n  \n\n Hope this helps. \n", "last_activity_date": "03/27/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/26/2013", "votes_count": 6, "last_edit_date": "03/27/2013", "id": "579", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "FileInputStream, FileOutputStream - check file for specific value/line/string", "parent_id": "15518443", "comment_count": 3, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "873875", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "yorkw", "owner_user_id": "873875"},{"body": " It is because your form method is  POST , and you are trying to  GET  ID.\nProbably ID returns null.\nMy suggestion is to put a hidden input in your form as with  name=\"ID\" , then read it in your posted page as  $_POST[\"ID\"];  \n", "last_activity_date": "03/28/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/28/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "580", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "PHP form : not updating mysql database", "parent_id": "15672308", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Jean", "owner_user_id": "2084262"},{"body": " The variables are scoped to the function, which means they  cannot  be accessed outside it unless they are explicitly passed out. Here are some options I can think of: \n\n \n  You could declare variables of the same name in an outer scope, such as the  window . Be careful, because if those variable names are used in other functions, they will all use the same \"global\" copy now and everything could break.  \n  You could add a \"variable-collector\" statement just before the final return of an anonymous function: \n\n  var collector = [];\n\n$(function () &123;\n   var Foo = \"Thing\",\n      Bar = \"Other Thing\",\n      Bag = new Widget(&123;name: \"Some Thing\", color: \"Purple\"&125;);\n   collector.push(&123;\"anonymousfunction1\": &123;Foo: Foo, Bar: Bar, Bag: Bag&125;&125;);\n   return something;\n&125;);\n  \n\n Then at the end of execution, you can inspect everything in the  collector  variable all you like. I made  collector  an array since I figured you might have multiple anonymous functions you want to learn about, or the function could be called multiple times (though it looks to me like a jQuery  ready  event, you never know).  \n  Just log the values to the console. This works in Chrome and Firefox (press F12) and may work in later versions of IE: \n\n  $(function () &123;\n   var Foo = \"Thing\",\n      Bar = \"Other Thing\",\n      Bag = new Widget(&123;name: \"Some Thing\", color: \"Purple\"&125;);\n   console.log(\"Foo\", Foo, \"Bar\", Bar, \"Bag\", Bag);\n   return something;\n&125;);\n   \n \n", "last_activity_date": "04/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/04/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "04/04/2013", "id": "581", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to inspect variable in an anonymous function?", "parent_id": "15820197", "comment_count": 0, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "57611", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "ErikE", "owner_user_id": "57611"},{"body": " You can introduce a new data transform to handle raw JSON. \n\n  DS.RESTAdapter.registerTransform(raw, &123;\n    deserialize: function(serialized) &123;\n        return serialized;\n    &125;,  \n    serialize: function(deserialized) &123;\n        return deserialized;\n    &125;   \n&125;);\n  \n\n Now you cab define your model with  raw  as the data type for  location . \n\n  App.Place = DS.Model.extend(&123;\n    name: DS.attr(string),\n    desc: DS.attr(string),\n    location: DS.attr(raw)\n&125;);\n  \n\n If your data from the server has the form \n\n  place: &123;\n    id: place,\n    name: foo,\n    desc: bar,\n    location: &123;\n        longitude: 1,\n        latitude: 2,\n        radius: 3\n    &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n then you can bind to  location.longitude , etc. in your template. Here is is fleshed out in  a jsfiddle . \n", "last_activity_date": "03/31/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/31/2013", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "582", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Ember Data and object graphs", "parent_id": "15731446", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "ahmacleod", "owner_user_id": "1691511"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " For those like me not wanting to recompile toolkit here is an easy workaround based on pantaloons answer. Simpy add Opened event handler: \n\n  &lt;toolkit:ContextMenu Opened=\"ContextMenu_Opened\"&gt;\n...\n&lt;/toolkit:ContextMenu&gt;\n  \n\n Event Handler code: \n\n  private void ContextMenu_Opened(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)\n&123;\n    var menu = (ContextMenu)sender;\n    var owner = (FrameworkElement)menu.Owner;\n    if (owner.DataContext != menu.DataContext)\n        menu.DataContext = owner.DataContext;\n\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/01/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/01/2013", "votes_count": 6, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "583", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Windows Phone Toolkit Context Menu Items have wrong object bound to them when an item is removed and then added", "parent_id": "15181441", "comment_count": 3, "score": 6, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "ghord", "owner_user_id": "855432"},{"body": " This is your query formated so it is more readable (at least to me): \n\n  update INVITATION i LEFT JOIN\n       REGISTRATION r\n       on i.id=r.INVITATION_id LEFT JOIN\n       FUNDING AS f on r.id=f.REGISTRATION_id \n    SET i.funding_travel_amount = \n            SUM(case when f.category = \"Other\" then sum(amount) \n                     when f.category = \"Airfare\" then sum(amount)\n                     when f.category = \"Mileage\" then sum(amount)\n                     else 0\n                end),\n       i.funding_travel = \"Custom\" \n     WHERE i.funding_hotel = \"Prepaid\" and\n           i.funding_travel = \"None\" and\n           i.funding_per_diem = \"None\"  and\n           (f.category = \"Other\" OR f.category =\"Airfare\" OR f.category= \"Mileage\") and\n           f.id is not null;\n  \n\n Onee problem is obvious -- you have sum statements within sums.  I would write this with a correlated subquery: \n\n  update INVITATION \n    SET funding_travel_amount = \n            (select SUM(case when f.category = \"Other\" then amount\n                             when f.category = \"Airfare\" then amount\n                             when f.category = \"Mileage\" then amount\n                             else 0\n                        end)\n             from Registration r join\n                  Funding f\n                  on r.id=f.REGISTRATION_id and\n                  invitation.id = r.invitation_id\n            ),\n       funding_travel = \"Custom\" \n     WHERE funding_hotel = \"Prepaid\" and\n           funding_travel = \"None\" and\n           funding_per_diem = \"None\" \n  \n\n This is not exactly the same, because it will update the amount even when none of the categories are avaialble.  You can fix that with an additional condition on the  where . \n", "last_activity_date": "04/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/01/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "04/03/2013", "id": "584", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "update using case and sum statements", "parent_id": "15747898", "comment_count": 2, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "1144035", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Gordon Linoff", "owner_user_id": "1144035"},{"body": " Different way: \n\n  if(!isset($array[0])) &123;\n    $array[0] = $array;\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/01/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/01/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "585", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Add a index key to existing array", "parent_id": "15751871", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "simonthesorcerer", "owner_user_id": "1130898"},{"body": " You can not use directly udtWChar2 as type , you need define type def or you need use as struct udtWChar2  \n\n Like : \n\n in .h \n\n vector  &lt; struct udtWChar2 >  pToWChar2(wstring u); \n\n vector  &lt; struct udtWChar2 >  m; \n\n in .cpp \n\n vector &lt; struct clsWString2::udtWChar2 >  clsWString2::pToWChar2(wstring u) \n", "last_activity_date": "04/02/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/02/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "586", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "C++ function with a struct vector as a return value", "parent_id": "15760217", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Venkata Naidu M", "owner_user_id": "2119671"},{"body": " You have to separate multiple  CREATE FUNCTION  calls with  GO  OR  ;  (or both - which one I prefer): \n\n  CREATE FUNCTION CalculateDistance\n        (@Longitude1 Decimal(8,5),\n        @Latitude1   Decimal(8,5),\n        @Longitude2  Decimal(8,5),\n        @Latitude2   Decimal(8,5))\n    Returns Float\n    AS BEGIN\n    Declare @Temp Float\n\n    Set @Temp = sin(@Latitude1/57.2957795130823) * sin(@Latitude2/57.2957795130823) + cos(@Latitude1/57.2957795130823) * cos(@Latitude2/57.2957795130823) * cos(@Longitude2/57.2957795130823 - @Longitude1/57.2957795130823)\n\n    if @Temp &gt; 1\n        Set @Temp = 1\n    Else If @Temp &lt; -1\n        Set @Temp = -1\n\n    Return (3958.75586574 * acos(@Temp) )\n\n    End;\nGO\n\n    -- FUNCTION \nCREATE FUNCTION LatitudePlusDistance(@StartLatitude Float, @Distance Float) Returns Float\n    AS BEGIN\n        Return (Select @StartLatitude + Sqrt(@Distance * @Distance / 4766.8999155991))\n    End\n\n    -- FUNCTION \n    CREATE FUNCTION LongitudePlusDistance\n        (@StartLongitude Float,\n        @StartLatitude Float,\n        @Distance Float)\n    Returns Float\n    AS BEGIN\n        Return (Select @StartLongitude + Sqrt(@Distance * @Distance / (4784.39411916406 * Cos(2 * @StartLatitude / 114.591559026165) * Cos(2 * @StartLatitude / 114.591559026165))))\n    End;\n\nGO\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/02/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/02/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "587", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Incorrect syntax near the keyword &#39;CREATE&#39; while creating function", "parent_id": "15769413", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "MarcinJuraszek", "owner_user_id": "1163867"},{"body": " You should check Lua stack every time before pushing into it. \nStack size is 20 by default, it should be manually enlarged if more space required. \n Lua manual  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/03/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "588", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Can I resize the max size of the stack when using lua_pushnumber", "parent_id": "15778678", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Egor Skriptunoff", "owner_user_id": "1847592"},{"body": " The core of the issue can be seen in this piece of code: \n\n  template &lt;typename T&gt;\nclass A&123;\n    B&lt;T&gt; b;\n&125;;\n\ntemplate &lt;typename T&gt;\nclass B&123;\n    A&lt;T&gt; a;\n&125;;\n  \n\n C++ is a language with value semantics, that means that  B&lt;T&gt; b;  represents an object of type  B&lt;T&gt;  (rather than a reference, like in Java or C# with reference types). That is,  A&lt;T&gt;   contains  a  B&lt;T&gt; . Now if you look at the definition of the  B  template you see that in turn it contains an  A&lt;T&gt;  sub object. This is basically impossible, as  A&lt;T&gt;  cannot possibly contain an object that contains  A&lt;T&gt; . What would be the size of an  A&lt;T&gt;  object? \n\n Without knowing the real problem to solve, I wont venture to recommend an approach, but you can consider using pointers ( A&lt;T&gt;  would contain a  pointer  to  B&lt;T&gt; , not a full  B&lt;T&gt;  sub object; or similarly,  B&lt;T&gt;  could contain a  pointer  to  A&lt;T&gt; ; or both), or references. But it might also be the case that a deeper redesign could make more sense. \n", "last_activity_date": "04/04/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/04/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "589", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Templates Calling Each Other&#39;s Functions", "parent_id": "15800905", "comment_count": 0, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "David Rodr\u00edguez - dribeas", "owner_user_id": "36565"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Try this instead: \n\n  SELECT company,\n  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2008 THEN amount ELSE 0 END) AS 2008,\n  MAX(CASE WHEN year = 2009 THEN amount ELSE 0 END) AS 2009\nFROM tbl\nGROUP BY company;\n  \n\n See it in action: \n\n \n  SQL Fiddle Demo  \n \n\n This will give you: \n\n  |  COMPANY | 2008 | 2009 |\n--------------------------\n| CompanyA |    5 |    0 |\n| CompanyB |    4 |    1 |\n| CompanyC |    0 |    4 |\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/06/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/06/2013", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "590", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to qualify the condition in a CASE expression (similar to WHERE clause)", "parent_id": "15848894", "comment_count": 2, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Mahmoud Gamal", "owner_user_id": "722783"},{"body": " A  ConcurrentHashMap  is designed so that it can be used by a large number of concurrent  Thread s. \n\n Now, if you used the methods provided by the standard  Map  interface you would probably write something like this \n\n    if(!map.containsKey(\"something\")) &123;\n      map.put(\"something\", \"a value\");\n  &125;\n  \n\n This looks good and seems to do the job but,  it is not thread safe . So you would then think, \"Ah, but I know about the  synchronized  keyword\" and change it to this \n\n    synchronized(map) &123;\n      if(!map.containsKey(\"something\")) &123;\n          map.put(\"something\", \"a value\");\n      &125;\n  &125;\n  \n\n Which fixes the issue. \n\n Now what you have done is  locked the entire map  for  both read and write  while you check if the key exists and then add it to the map. \n\n This is a very crude solution. Now you could implement your own solution with double checked locks and re-locking on the key etc. but that is  a lot  of  very complicated  code that is very prone to bugs. \n\n So, instead you use the solution provided by the JDK. \n\n The  ConcurrentHashMap  is a clever implementation that divides the  Map  into regions and locks them individually so that you can have concurrent, thread safe, reads and writes of the map without external locking. \n\n Like all other methods in the implementation  putIfAbsent  locks the keys region and not the whole  Map  and therefore allows other things to go on in other regions in the meantime. \n", "last_activity_date": "04/06/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/06/2013", "votes_count": 3, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "591", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "concurrent hashMap putIfAbsent method functionality", "parent_id": "15850803", "comment_count": 0, "score": 3, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Boris the Spider", "owner_user_id": "2071828"},{"body": " The Trigonometrys Calculator variable, cal, is null because it was never initialized with the current Calculator instance. You need to get the Calculator instance into the Trigonometry class so that the Trig class can call the public methods of the Calculator. One way to do this is via a constructor parameter, and another way is via a setter method such as  setCalculator(Calculator calculator) &123;...&125; . An example of the constructor parameter technique: \n\n in Calculator.java: \n\n  Trigonometry t = new Trigonometry(this);\n  \n\n and in Trigonometry class: \n\n  // constructor now accepts a Calculator parameter\npublic Trigonmetry(Calculator calculator) &123;\n  // initialize the cal field with the current Calculator instance\n  cal = calculator; \n  InitialUI();\n&125;\n  \n\n Also: \n\n \n Dont use  setBounds(...)  and null layout as per camickrs recommendation. \n Instead read up on the use of layout managers and then use nested JPanels that each use an appropriate layout manager. \n Dont use more than one JFrame. The second Trig window should be a JDialog (also per camickrs recommendation). \n Learn and use Java coding conventions. Class names start with an upper case letter and method and variable names a lower-case letter. \n When asking questions here, try to pare your code down to the bare minimum that shows your problem, still allows your code to compile and run, but contains no code unrelated to your problem. 95% of your current code posted above is unnecessary to solving the problem and distracting for us. \n \n\n Also: \n\n \n If you only want the Trigonometry instance to open under the control of Calculator, then dont have the code to show it called by Trigonometry but rather by Calculator.  In other words, dont have Trigonometry call  setVisible(true)  on itself, but rather have Calculator call this on the Trigonometry instance. \n \n\n In Calculator: \n\n  class MenuListener implements ActionListener &123;\n  public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) &123;\n     t.setVisible(true);\n     trigOpen = true;\n  &125;\n&125;\n  \n\n In Trigonometry: \n\n  public final void InitialUI() &123; // this should be named initialUi()\n\n  // ..... code deleted for brevity\n\n  panel.add(baTan);\n  add(panel);\n  // !!  setVisible(true); // *** dont call this here ***\n  ActionListener operandListener = new OperandListener();\n\n  // ..... code deleted for brevity\n\n&125;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/06/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/06/2013", "votes_count": 4, "last_edit_date": "04/06/2013", "id": "592", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Calculator: Cannot use ActionListener in a pop up window from my main GUI", "parent_id": "15852637", "comment_count": 4, "score": 4, "last_editor_user_id": "522444", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Hovercraft Full Of Eels", "owner_user_id": "522444"},{"body": " Get  madexcept , or any other similar tool and post the stack of the application. Also, this should be a problem with codecs and other applications installed on the machine, even the movie is played in XPs Windows Media Player.  \n\n As several suggestions : use the Windows Media Player ActiveX or the  ActiveX plugin  from VideoLan. \n\n Also be sure to follow this  http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/Libraries/XE3/en/FMX.Media.TMediaPlayerControl  and  http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE3/en/Building_a_Basic_Media_Player  \n\n PS: Be aware that FireMonkey is not VCL -  http://docwiki.embarcadero.com/RADStudio/XE3/en/Converting_from_VCL_to_FireMonkey  and do not mix these two. (Im just suspecting youre doing it, so without the code I can not be sure of it...) \n", "last_activity_date": "04/07/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/07/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "593", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Play video in Firemonkey on Windows XP", "parent_id": "15860468", "comment_count": 3, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "RBA", "owner_user_id": "368364"}]'
curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Here is simple way to using  lapply ,  rbind  and  do.call  \n\n  ptl\n## [[1]]\n## x\n##         21         41         42         43         52         71         81         82 \n## 0.02007456 0.58158876 0.22483510 0.09349011 0.05248064 0.01204474 0.00544881 0.01003728 \n## \n## [[2]]\n## x\n##         21         41         42         43         52         71         90 \n## 0.01175122 0.36973345 0.34107194 0.03066781 0.08655775 0.01633706 0.14388077 \n## \n## [[3]]\n## x\n##          21          22          23          41          42 \n## 0.043254082 0.008307075 0.016614151 0.930392438 0.001432254 \n## \n## [[4]]\n## x\n##         21         22         31         41         42         43         81 \n## 0.10028653 0.03123209 0.00487106 0.66103152 0.03037249 0.01604585 0.15616046 \n## \n## [[5]]\n## x\n##           21           41           42           43           81 \n## 0.0662080825 0.8291774147 0.0005732302 0.0865577529 0.0174835196 \n## \n## [[6]]\n## x\n##          21          22          31          41          42          43          81 \n## 0.081948424 0.002292264 0.006303725 0.825501433 0.029226361 0.020630372 0.034097421 \n## \n\n\n# Get unique names of all columns in tables in the list\nresCol &lt;- unique(unlist(lapply(ptl, names)))\n\n# Get dimensions of desired result\nnresCol &lt;- length(resCol)\nnresRow &lt;- length(ptl)\n\n# Create Template data.frame row\nDF &lt;- as.data.frame(matrix(rep(0, nresCol), nrow = 1, dimnames = list(1, resCol)))\n\n# for every table in list, create copy of DF, fill it appropriately, then rbind result together using do.call\n\nresult &lt;- do.call(rbind, lapply(ptl, function(x) &123;\n    retDF &lt;- DF\n    retDF[, names(x)] &lt;- x\n    return(retDF)\n&125;))\n\n# rename rows(optional)\nrownames(result) &lt;- 1:nrow(result)\n\nresult\n##           21        41           42         43         52         71         81         82        90       