curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " find the solution, but i thing this isnt the best solution \n\n  \nchmod +rx -R /home/fabriciols/\n  \n\n i read that apache only need READ perm on dir, but it seems to need execute perm too :D \n", "last_activity_date": "12/11/2009", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/11/2009", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "667", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "django - apache integration", "parent_id": "1888737", "comment_count": 1, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "fabriciols", "owner_user_id": "216180"},{"body": " You can use the address fields within sed to limit the replacement to lines that match a particular pattern. So simply add  /CARD_NUMBER=/  to the start of your expression, giving \n\n  sed -e :a -e \"/CARD_NUMBER=/s/[0-9]E&#39\\\\&#39([0-9]E&#39\\\\&#39\\{4E&#39\\\\&#39\\}E&#39\\\\&#39)/E&#39\\\\&#39*E&#39\\\\&#391/;ta\" $today_temp_log\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "02/18/2010", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/18/2010", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "668", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Regular expression using sed", "parent_id": "2282716", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Beano", "owner_user_id": "104172"},{"body": " As written, func is a member of Foo and a method of Foo instances such as your f. However, it can&#39t be successfully called because it doesn&#39t accept at least one argument. \n\n func is in f&#39s namespace and has a _ call_ () method. In other words, it is enough of a method that Python tries to call it