curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " Indeed the question doesn&#39t make sense but I believe it&#39s not too hard to guess\nwhat the question is about. \n\n My guess for a rephrasal: why should we use inheritance between A (super) &amp; B (sub) instead of creating them separately and instantiate A from B. \n\n The main reasons for inheritance I would say: \n\n \n Code reusability \n Polymorphism \n Code extension made easier, very much related to 1) \n ... \n ... \n \n", "last_activity_date": "03/14/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "03/14/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "766", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "why should we use inheritance between A (super) &amp; B (sub) instead of creating them separately and instantiate A from B?", "parent_id": "9701049", "comment_count": 0, "score": 2, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "hajder", "owner_user_id": "1132333"},{"body": " How about an image button? \n\n  &lt;ItemTemplate&gt;\n        &lt;asp:ImageButton ID=\"ImageButton1\" runat=\"server\" \n            ImageUrl=\"~/Images/smallcross.gif\" onclick=\"ImageButton1_Click\" /&gt;\n&lt;/ItemTemplate&gt;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/27/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/27/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "767", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Add a clickable image to a GridView in ASP.Net", "parent_id": "10353115", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Steve Wellens", "owner_user_id": "479869"},{"body": " Use the following code: \n\n  &lt;asp:ImageButton ID=\"hea