o be able to install ruby 1.9.3.\nUnfortunately Lion does not include anymore gcc-4-2, just the llvm version: \n\n  lrwxr-xr-x  1 root  wheel  12 15 feb 17:21 /usr/bin/gcc -&gt; llvm-gcc-4.2\n  \n\n If you have Lion but upgraded from Snow Leopard it is likely that you still have gcc-4.2 If you have a brand new installation of Lion you should download gcc-4.2. I recommned downloading this package. \n\n  https://github.com/kennethreitz/osx-gcc-installer\n  \n\n Check that you have gcc-4.2 installed now: \n\n  -rwxr-xr-x  1 root  wheel  113024 16 may  2011 /usr/bin/gcc-4.2\nlrwxr-xr-x  1 root  wheel      12 15 feb 17:21 /usr/bin/gcc -&gt; llvm-gcc-4.2\n  \n\n Now you can install ruby 1.9.3 as usual: \n\n  rvm install 1.9.3\nrvm use 1.9.3 --default\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "02/16/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/16/2012", "votes_count": 13, "last_edit_date": "02/16/2012", "id": "862", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How can I install Ruby 1.9.3 in Mac OS X Lion?", "parent_id": "8139138", "comment_count": 3, "score": 13, "last_editor_user_id": "84678", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Marc M", "owner_user_id": "84678"},{"body": " Be careful with catching the errorLevel = 1 from robocopy.  It will be 1 even if robocopy fails, giving you a false positive.  I had to go back to xcopy unfortunately, but at least I know what&#39s going on. \n", "last_activity_date": "02/26/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "02/26/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "863", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Using robocopy with Visual Studio 2010 Post-build and Pre-build events", "parent_id": "5470828", "comment_count": 2, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date":