curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " This works (for original example): \n\n  $url = &#39http://www.stackoverflow.com/tags/thisthat/againthisthat/againandagainthisthat/mypage.html\n$urlBitsArray = explode(&#39/&#39, $url);\n$urlBitsCount = count($urlBitsArray);\n$newUrl = implode(&#39/&#39, array($urlBitsArray[&#390&#39], $urlBitsArray[&#391&#39], $urlBitsArray[&#392&#39], $urlBitsArray[&#393&#39], &#39.....&#39, $urlBitsArray[$urlBitsCount - 2], $urlBitsArray[$urlBitsCount - 1]));\necho $newUrl;\n  \n\n Basic if more than 70 take first 32 chars, last 32 chars and &#39......&#39 in the middle: \n\n  $url = &#39http://www.stackoverflow.com/tags/thisthat/againthisthat/againandagainthisthat/mypage.html \n\nif (strlen($url) &gt; 70) \\{\n    $url = substr($url, 0, 31).&#39......&#39.substr($url, strlen($url) - 33);\n\\}\n\necho $url;\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "04/04/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "04/04/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "04/04/2012", "id": "971", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to minimize url link in search result", "parent_id": "10008104", "comment_count": 4, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "1237595", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Ing", "owner_user_id": "1237595"},{"body": " For insert and updates MySQL has a good, alternative solution - \"ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE\". It does what you want safely in a single query: \n\n  INSERT .... ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE\n  \n\n (also the key must be set as unique in this scenario) \n\n  http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/insert-on-duplicate.html  \n", "last_activity_date": "05/04/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "05/03/2012", "votes_count": 1, "last_edit_date": "05/04/2012", "id": "972", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "