curl "http://localhost:7049/stackoverflow/docs" -i -X PUT -d '[{"body": " I have the same problem with Serbian keyboard - which is the same as Slovenian.\nSomeone mentioned that the shortcut for the  GoToContainingDeclaration  feature that overrides Find is  Ctrl + [ . Well, guess what - on our keyboards,  [  is typed as  AltGr + F . Most likely that is why Resharper assigns the command that would normally go to  Ctrl + [  to  Ctrl + F . \n\n Now the workaround (if not the solution): \n\n \n Reset the VS keyboard shortcuts (Tools> Options> Keyboard) \n Temporarily set US keyboard \n Set Resharper keyboard shortcuts (Resharper> Options> Keyboard&amp;Menus) \n Go back to your keyboard of choice \n \n", "last_activity_date": "11/15/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "11/15/2012", "votes_count": 9, "last_edit_date": "11/15/2012", "id": "981", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "ReSharper breaks keyboard shortcuts for &quot;Find&quot; and &quot;Find in Files&quot;", "parent_id": "2789095", "comment_count": 2, "score": 8, "last_editor_user_id": "974789", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Aleksandar Vasi\u0107", "owner_user_id": "1826566"},{"body": " You are currently sorting on code, but as text and not as a number. To sort it as you want, you have to write a comparison function that indicates whether one code is bigger than another: \n\n  function sortByCode($a, $b) &123;\n    $aParts = explode(-, $a[Code]);\n    $bParts = explode(-, $b[Code]);\n    for ($i = 0; $i &lt; count($aParts); $i++) &123;\n        if ($aParts[$i] &lt; $bParts[$i]) &123;\n            return -1;\n        &125; else if ($aParts[$i] &gt; $bParts[$i]) &123;\n            return 1;\n        &125;\n    &125;\n    return 0;\n&125;\n\nusort($myArray, sortByCode);\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "11/28/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "11/28/2012", "votes_count": 2, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "982", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Sorting multidimentional Array Keys As Number", "parent_id": "13601469", "comment_count": 1, "score": 1, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Sjoerd", "owner_user_id": "182971"},{"body": " You can use  isOpen()  to check, so in your case, that would be  \n\n  database.isOpen()\n  \n\n just a tip, when working with Java based API (or any APIs for that matter), learning to use the documentation of the API is key. The docs will tell you which methods are available for any given class. For example, you got a instance of the class SQLiteDatabase. Checking the javadocs below \n\n  http://developer.android.com/reference/android/database/sqlite/SQLiteDatabase.html  \n\n its pretty trivial to identify the method you are looking for.  \n", "last_activity_date": "12/07/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/07/2012", "votes_count": 7, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "983", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Check sqlite database is open or closed in android", "parent_id": "13760547", "comment_count": 1, "score": 6, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "JustDanyul", "owner_user_id": "826532"},{"body": " It seems you analyze some existing code and try to understand why there is synchronization. \n\n Are the part1 and part2 code in the same function? \n\n In the second part the synchronization does not make sense. Creating the customer object and then synchronizing has no effect. A second thread would create a new customer object and lock on that object. \n\n If you need to change existing code you can write a testcase and span may threads and remove the synchronization to see if you can force a multithreading issue. \n", "last_activity_date": "12/13/2012", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "12/13/2012", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "984", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "Java Synchronization processes", "parent_id": "13855593", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "opi", "owner_user_id": "1863377"},{"body": " In my case, I found another solution: is to create an ArrayList and put on it all the links on every for loop. Thats a lot easier. \n", "last_activity_date": "01/03/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/03/2013", "votes_count": 0, "last_edit_date": "01/01/1970", "id": "985", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How to get a HashMap value with three values", "parent_id": "14148331", "comment_count": 0, "score": 0, "last_editor_user_id": "0", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "androniennn", "owner_user_id": "656147"},{"body": " You can use the taskkill utility. \n\n  taskkill /PID 8436\n  \n", "last_activity_date": "01/09/2013", "accepted_answer_id": "0", "creation_date": "01/09/2013", "votes_count": 9, "last_edit_date": "01/09/2013", "id": "986", "favorite_count": 0, "last_editor_display_name": "", "closed_date": "01/01/1970", "view_count": 0, "title": "How do I kill a rails webrick server?", "parent_id": "14244288", "comment_count": 5, "score": 7, "last_editor_user_id": "563041", "post_type_id": "2", "community_owned_date": "01/01/1970", "tags": "", "answer_count": 0, "author_name": "Daniel Evans", "owner_user_id": "563041"},{"body": " Use  NSDateFormatter , in your  .h  h